45def set_range_metadata(builder, load, lower_bound, upper_bound): 

46 """ 

47 Set the "range" metadata on a load instruction. 

48 Note the interval is in the form [lower_bound, upper_bound). 

49 """ 

50 range_operands = [Constant(load.type, lower_bound), 

51 Constant(load.type, upper_bound)] 

52 md = builder.module.add_metadata(range_operands) 

53 load.set_metadata("range", md) 

54 

55 

56def mark_positive(builder, load): 

57 """ 

58 Mark the result of a load instruction as positive (or zero). 

59 """ 

60 upper_bound = (1 << (load.type.width - 1)) - 1 

61 set_range_metadata(builder, load, 0, upper_bound)

64def make_array(array_type): 

65 """ 

66 Return the Structure representation of the given *array_type* 

67 (an instance of types.ArrayCompatible). 

68 

69 Note this does not call __array_wrap__ in case a new array structure 

70 is being created (rather than populated). 

71 """ 

72 real_array_type = array_type.as_array 

73 base = cgutils.create_struct_proxy(real_array_type) 

74 ndim = real_array_type.ndim 

75 

76 class ArrayStruct(base): 

77 

78 def _make_refs(self, ref): 

79 sig = signature(real_array_type, array_type) 

80 try: 

81 array_impl = self._context.get_function('__array__', sig) 

82 except NotImplementedError: 

83 return super(ArrayStruct, self)._make_refs(ref) 

84 

85 # Return a wrapped structure and its unwrapped reference 

86 datamodel = self._context.data_model_manager[array_type] 

87 be_type = self._get_be_type(datamodel) 

88 if ref is None: 

89 outer_ref = cgutils.alloca_once(self._builder, be_type, 

90 zfill=True) 

91 else: 

92 outer_ref = ref 

93 # NOTE: __array__ is called with a pointer and expects a pointer 

94 # in return! 

95 ref = array_impl(self._builder, (outer_ref,)) 

96 return outer_ref, ref 

97 

98 @property 

99 def shape(self): 

100 """ 

101 Override .shape to inform LLVM that its elements are all positive. 

102 """ 

103 builder = self._builder 

104 if ndim == 0: 

105 return base.__getattr__(self, "shape") 

106 

107 # Unfortunately, we can't use llvm.assume as its presence can 

108 # seriously pessimize performance, 

109 # *and* the range metadata currently isn't improving anything here, 

110 # see https://llvm.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=23848 ! 

111 ptr = self._get_ptr_by_name("shape") 

112 dims = [] 

113 for i in range(ndim): 

114 dimptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, ptr, 0, i) 

115 load = builder.load(dimptr) 

116 dims.append(load) 

117 mark_positive(builder, load) 

118 

119 return cgutils.pack_array(builder, dims) 

120 

121 return ArrayStruct

149def fix_integer_index(context, builder, idxty, idx, size): 

150 """ 

151 Fix the integer index' type and value for the given dimension size. 

152 """ 

153 if idxty.signed: 

154 ind = context.cast(builder, idx, idxty, types.intp) 

155 ind = slicing.fix_index(builder, ind, size) 

156 else: 

157 ind = context.cast(builder, idx, idxty, types.uintp)

161def normalize_index(context, builder, idxty, idx): 

162 """ 

163 Normalize the index type and value. 0-d arrays are converted to scalars. 

164 """ 

165 if isinstance(idxty, types.Array) and idxty.ndim == 0: 

166 assert isinstance(idxty.dtype, types.Integer) 

167 idxary = make_array(idxty)(context, builder, idx) 

168 idxval = load_item(context, builder, idxty, idxary.data) 

169 return idxty.dtype, idxval 

170 else: 

171 return idxty, idx

174def normalize_indices(context, builder, index_types, indices): 

175 """ 

176 Same as normalize_index(), but operating on sequences of 

177 index types and values. 

178 """ 

179 if len(indices): 

180 index_types, indices = zip(*[normalize_index(context, builder, idxty, 

181 idx) 

182 for idxty, idx in zip(index_types, indices) 

183 ]) 

184 return index_types, indices

187def populate_array(array, data, shape, strides, itemsize, meminfo, 

188 parent=None): 

189 """ 

190 Helper function for populating array structures. 

191 This avoids forgetting to set fields. 

192 

193 *shape* and *strides* can be Python tuples or LLVM arrays. 

194 """ 

195 context = array._context 

196 builder = array._builder 

197 datamodel = array._datamodel 

198 # doesn't matter what this array type instance is, it's just to get the 

199 # fields for the datamodel of the standard array type in this context 

200 standard_array = types.Array(types.float64, 1, 'C') 

201 standard_array_type_datamodel = context.data_model_manager[standard_array] 

202 required_fields = set(standard_array_type_datamodel._fields) 

203 datamodel_fields = set(datamodel._fields) 

204 # Make sure that the presented array object has a data model that is close 

205 # enough to an array for this function to proceed. 

206 if (required_fields & datamodel_fields) != required_fields: 

207 missing = required_fields - datamodel_fields 

208 msg = (f"The datamodel for type {array._fe_type} is missing " 

209 f"field{'s' if len(missing) > 1 else ''} {missing}.") 

210 raise ValueError(msg) 

211 

212 if meminfo is None: 

213 meminfo = Constant(context.get_value_type( 

214 datamodel.get_type('meminfo')), None) 

215 

216 intp_t = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

217 if isinstance(shape, (tuple, list)): 

218 shape = cgutils.pack_array(builder, shape, intp_t) 

219 if isinstance(strides, (tuple, list)): 

220 strides = cgutils.pack_array(builder, strides, intp_t) 

221 if isinstance(itemsize, int): 

222 itemsize = intp_t(itemsize) 

223 

224 attrs = dict(shape=shape, 

225 strides=strides, 

226 data=data, 

227 itemsize=itemsize, 

228 meminfo=meminfo,) 

229 

230 # Set `parent` attribute 

231 if parent is None: 

232 attrs['parent'] = Constant(context.get_value_type( 

233 datamodel.get_type('parent')), None) 

234 else: 

235 attrs['parent'] = parent 

236 # Calc num of items from shape 

237 nitems = context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

238 unpacked_shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, shape, shape.type.count) 

239 # (note empty shape => 0d array therefore nitems = 1) 

240 for axlen in unpacked_shape: 

241 nitems = builder.mul(nitems, axlen, flags=['nsw']) 

242 attrs['nitems'] = nitems 

243 

244 # Make sure that we have all the fields 

245 got_fields = set(attrs.keys()) 

246 if got_fields != required_fields: 

247 raise ValueError("missing {0}".format(required_fields - got_fields)) 

248 

249 # Set field value 

250 for k, v in attrs.items(): 

251 setattr(array, k, v) 

252 

253 return array

256def update_array_info(aryty, array): 

257 """ 

258 Update some auxiliary information in *array* after some of its fields 

259 were changed. `itemsize` and `nitems` are updated. 

260 """ 

261 context = array._context 

262 builder = array._builder 

263 

264 # Calc num of items from shape 

265 nitems = context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

266 unpacked_shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, array.shape, aryty.ndim) 

267 for axlen in unpacked_shape: 

268 nitems = builder.mul(nitems, axlen, flags=['nsw']) 

269 array.nitems = nitems 

270 

271 array.itemsize = context.get_constant(types.intp, 

272 get_itemsize(context, aryty))

327def _getitem_array_single_int(context, builder, return_type, aryty, ary, idx): 

328 """ Evaluate `ary[idx]`, where idx is a single int. """ 

329 # optimized form of _getitem_array_generic 

330 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape, count=aryty.ndim) 

331 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides, count=aryty.ndim) 

332 offset = builder.mul(strides[0], idx) 

333 dataptr = cgutils.pointer_add(builder, ary.data, offset) 

334 view_shapes = shapes[1:] 

335 view_strides = strides[1:] 

336 

337 if isinstance(return_type, types.Buffer): 

338 # Build array view 

339 retary = make_view(context, builder, aryty, ary, return_type, 

340 dataptr, view_shapes, view_strides) 

341 return retary._getvalue() 

342 else: 

343 # Load scalar from 0-d result 

344 assert not view_shapes 

345 return load_item(context, builder, aryty, dataptr)

348@lower_builtin('iternext', types.ArrayIterator) 

349@iternext_impl(RefType.BORROWED) 

350def iternext_array(context, builder, sig, args, result): 

351 [iterty] = sig.args 

352 [iter] = args 

353 arrayty = iterty.array_type 

354 

355 iterobj = context.make_helper(builder, iterty, value=iter) 

356 ary = make_array(arrayty)(context, builder, value=iterobj.array) 

357 

358 nitems, = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape, count=1) 

359 

360 index = builder.load(iterobj.index) 

361 is_valid = builder.icmp_signed('<', index, nitems) 

362 result.set_valid(is_valid) 

363 

364 with builder.if_then(is_valid): 

365 value = _getitem_array_single_int( 

366 context, builder, iterty.yield_type, arrayty, ary, index 

367 ) 

368 result.yield_(value) 

369 nindex = cgutils.increment_index(builder, index) 

370 builder.store(nindex, iterobj.index)

376def basic_indexing(context, builder, aryty, ary, index_types, indices, 

377 boundscheck=None): 

378 """ 

379 Perform basic indexing on the given array. 

380 A (data pointer, shapes, strides) tuple is returned describing 

381 the corresponding view. 

382 """ 

383 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

384 one = context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

385 

386 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape, aryty.ndim) 

387 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides, aryty.ndim) 

388 

389 output_indices = [] 

390 output_shapes = [] 

391 output_strides = [] 

392 

393 num_newaxes = len([idx for idx in index_types if is_nonelike(idx)]) 

394 ax = 0 

395 for indexval, idxty in zip(indices, index_types): 

396 if idxty is types.ellipsis: 

397 # Fill up missing dimensions at the middle 

398 n_missing = aryty.ndim - len(indices) + 1 + num_newaxes 

399 for i in range(n_missing): 

400 output_indices.append(zero) 

401 output_shapes.append(shapes[ax]) 

402 output_strides.append(strides[ax]) 

403 ax += 1 

404 continue 

405 # Regular index value 

406 if isinstance(idxty, types.SliceType): 

407 slice = context.make_helper(builder, idxty, value=indexval) 

408 slicing.guard_invalid_slice(context, builder, idxty, slice) 

409 slicing.fix_slice(builder, slice, shapes[ax]) 

410 output_indices.append(slice.start) 

411 sh = slicing.get_slice_length(builder, slice) 

412 st = slicing.fix_stride(builder, slice, strides[ax]) 

413 output_shapes.append(sh) 

414 output_strides.append(st) 

415 elif isinstance(idxty, types.Integer): 

416 ind = fix_integer_index(context, builder, idxty, indexval, 

417 shapes[ax]) 

418 if boundscheck: 

419 cgutils.do_boundscheck(context, builder, ind, shapes[ax], ax) 

420 output_indices.append(ind) 

421 elif is_nonelike(idxty): 

422 output_shapes.append(one) 

423 output_strides.append(zero) 

424 ax -= 1 

425 else: 

426 raise NotImplementedError("unexpected index type: %s" % (idxty,)) 

427 ax += 1 

428 

429 # Fill up missing dimensions at the end 

430 assert ax <= aryty.ndim 

431 while ax < aryty.ndim: 

432 output_shapes.append(shapes[ax]) 

433 output_strides.append(strides[ax]) 

434 ax += 1 

435 

436 # No need to check wraparound, as negative indices were already 

437 # fixed in the loop above. 

438 dataptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer(context, builder, aryty, ary, 

439 output_indices, 

440 wraparound=False, boundscheck=False) 

441 return (dataptr, output_shapes, output_strides)

444def make_view(context, builder, aryty, ary, return_type, 

445 data, shapes, strides): 

446 """ 

447 Build a view over the given array with the given parameters. 

448 """ 

449 retary = make_array(return_type)(context, builder) 

450 populate_array(retary, 

451 data=data, 

452 shape=shapes, 

453 strides=strides, 

454 itemsize=ary.itemsize, 

455 meminfo=ary.meminfo, 

456 parent=ary.parent) 

457 return retary

460def _getitem_array_generic(context, builder, return_type, aryty, ary, 

461 index_types, indices): 

462 """ 

463 Return the result of indexing *ary* with the given *indices*, 

464 returning either a scalar or a view. 

465 """ 

466 dataptr, view_shapes, view_strides = \ 

467 basic_indexing(context, builder, aryty, ary, index_types, indices, 

468 boundscheck=context.enable_boundscheck) 

469 

470 if isinstance(return_type, types.Buffer): 

471 # Build array view 

472 retary = make_view(context, builder, aryty, ary, return_type, 

473 dataptr, view_shapes, view_strides) 

474 return retary._getvalue() 

475 else: 

476 # Load scalar from 0-d result 

477 assert not view_shapes 

478 return load_item(context, builder, aryty, dataptr)

498@lower_builtin(operator.getitem, types.Buffer, types.BaseTuple) 

499def getitem_array_tuple(context, builder, sig, args): 

500 """ 

501 Basic or advanced indexing with a tuple. 

502 """ 

503 aryty, tupty = sig.args 

504 ary, tup = args 

505 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, ary) 

506 

507 index_types = tupty.types 

508 indices = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, tup, count=len(tupty)) 

509 

510 index_types, indices = normalize_indices(context, builder, 

511 index_types, indices) 

512 

513 if any(isinstance(ty, types.Array) for ty in index_types): 

514 # Advanced indexing 

515 return fancy_getitem(context, builder, sig, args, 

516 aryty, ary, index_types, indices) 

517 

518 res = _getitem_array_generic(context, builder, sig.return_type, 

519 aryty, ary, index_types, indices) 

520 return impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, sig.return_type, res)

523@lower_builtin(operator.setitem, types.Buffer, types.Any, types.Any) 

524def setitem_array(context, builder, sig, args): 

525 """ 

526 array[a] = scalar_or_array 

527 array[a,..,b] = scalar_or_array 

528 """ 

529 aryty, idxty, valty = sig.args 

530 ary, idx, val = args 

531 

532 if isinstance(idxty, types.BaseTuple): 

533 index_types = idxty.types 

534 indices = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, idx, count=len(idxty)) 

535 else: 

536 index_types = (idxty,) 

537 indices = (idx,) 

538 

539 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, ary) 

540 

541 # First try basic indexing to see if a single array location is denoted. 

542 index_types, indices = normalize_indices(context, builder, 

543 index_types, indices) 

544 try: 

545 dataptr, shapes, strides = \ 

546 basic_indexing(context, builder, aryty, ary, index_types, indices, 

547 boundscheck=context.enable_boundscheck) 

548 except NotImplementedError: 

549 use_fancy_indexing = True 

550 else: 

551 use_fancy_indexing = bool(shapes) 

552 

553 if use_fancy_indexing: 

554 # Index describes a non-trivial view => use generic slice assignment 

555 # (NOTE: this also handles scalar broadcasting) 

556 return fancy_setslice(context, builder, sig, args, 

557 index_types, indices) 

558 

559 # Store source value the given location 

560 val = context.cast(builder, val, valty, aryty.dtype) 

561 store_item(context, builder, aryty, val, dataptr)

575@lower_builtin("array.item", types.Array) 

576def array_item(context, builder, sig, args): 

577 aryty, = sig.args 

578 ary, = args 

579 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, ary) 

580 

581 nitems = ary.nitems 

582 with builder.if_then(builder.icmp_signed('!=', nitems, nitems.type(1)), 

583 likely=False): 

584 msg = "item(): can only convert an array of size 1 to a Python scalar" 

585 context.call_conv.return_user_exc(builder, ValueError, (msg,)) 

586 

587 return load_item(context, builder, aryty, ary.data)

635 raise NotImplementedError 

636 

637 def get_index_bounds(self): 

638 """ 

639 Return a half-open [lower, upper) range of indices this dimension 

640 is guaranteed not to step out of. 

641 """ 

642 raise NotImplementedError 

643 

644 def loop_head(self): 

645 """ 

646 Start indexation loop. Return a (index, count) tuple. 

647 *index* is an integer LLVM value representing the index over this 

648 dimension. 

649 *count* is either an integer LLVM value representing the current 

650 iteration count, or None if this dimension should be omitted from 

651 the indexation result. 

652 """ 

653 raise NotImplementedError 

654 

655 def loop_tail(self): 

656 """ 

657 Finish indexation loop. 

658 """ 

659 raise NotImplementedError

662class EntireIndexer(Indexer): 

663 """ 

664 Compute indices along an entire array dimension. 

665 """ 

666 

667 def __init__(self, context, builder, aryty, ary, dim): 

668 self.context = context 

669 self.builder = builder 

670 self.aryty = aryty 

671 self.ary = ary 

672 self.dim = dim 

673 self.ll_intp = self.context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

674 

675 def prepare(self): 

676 builder = self.builder 

677 self.size = builder.extract_value(self.ary.shape, self.dim) 

678 self.index = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

679 self.bb_start = builder.append_basic_block() 

680 self.bb_end = builder.append_basic_block() 

681 

682 def get_size(self): 

683 return self.size 

684 

685 def get_shape(self): 

686 return (self.size,) 

687 

688 def get_index_bounds(self): 

689 # [0, size) 

690 return (self.ll_intp(0), self.size) 

691 

692 def loop_head(self): 

693 builder = self.builder 

694 # Initialize loop variable 

695 self.builder.store(Constant(self.ll_intp, 0), self.index) 

696 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

697 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_start) 

698 cur_index = builder.load(self.index) 

699 with builder.if_then(builder.icmp_signed('>=', cur_index, self.size), 

700 likely=False): 

701 builder.branch(self.bb_end) 

702 return cur_index, cur_index 

703 

704 def loop_tail(self): 

705 builder = self.builder 

706 next_index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, builder.load(self.index)) 

707 builder.store(next_index, self.index) 

708 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

709 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_end)

743class IntegerArrayIndexer(Indexer): 

744 """ 

745 Compute indices from an array of integer indices. 

746 """ 

747 

748 def __init__(self, context, builder, idxty, idxary, size): 

749 self.context = context 

750 self.builder = builder 

751 self.idxty = idxty 

752 self.idxary = idxary 

753 self.size = size 

754 assert idxty.ndim == 1 

755 self.ll_intp = self.context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

756 

757 def prepare(self): 

758 builder = self.builder 

759 self.idx_size = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, self.idxary.shape)[0] 

760 self.idx_index = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

761 self.bb_start = builder.append_basic_block() 

762 self.bb_end = builder.append_basic_block() 

763 

764 def get_size(self): 

765 return self.idx_size 

766 

767 def get_shape(self): 

768 return (self.idx_size,) 

769 

770 def get_index_bounds(self): 

771 # Pessimal heuristic, as we don't want to scan for the min and max 

772 return (self.ll_intp(0), self.size) 

773 

774 def loop_head(self): 

775 builder = self.builder 

776 # Initialize loop variable 

777 self.builder.store(Constant(self.ll_intp, 0), self.idx_index) 

778 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

779 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_start) 

780 cur_index = builder.load(self.idx_index) 

781 with builder.if_then( 

782 builder.icmp_signed('>=', cur_index, self.idx_size), 

783 likely=False 

784 ): 

785 builder.branch(self.bb_end) 

786 # Load the actual index from the array of indices 

787 index = _getitem_array_single_int( 

788 self.context, builder, self.idxty.dtype, self.idxty, self.idxary, 

789 cur_index 

790 ) 

791 index = fix_integer_index(self.context, builder, 

792 self.idxty.dtype, index, self.size) 

793 return index, cur_index 

794 

795 def loop_tail(self): 

796 builder = self.builder 

797 next_index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, 

798 builder.load(self.idx_index)) 

799 builder.store(next_index, self.idx_index) 

800 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

801 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_end)

804class BooleanArrayIndexer(Indexer): 

805 """ 

806 Compute indices from an array of boolean predicates. 

807 """ 

808 

809 def __init__(self, context, builder, idxty, idxary): 

810 self.context = context 

811 self.builder = builder 

812 self.idxty = idxty 

813 self.idxary = idxary 

814 assert idxty.ndim == 1 

815 self.ll_intp = self.context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

816 self.zero = Constant(self.ll_intp, 0) 

817 

818 def prepare(self): 

819 builder = self.builder 

820 self.size = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, self.idxary.shape)[0] 

821 self.idx_index = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

822 self.count = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

823 self.bb_start = builder.append_basic_block() 

824 self.bb_tail = builder.append_basic_block() 

825 self.bb_end = builder.append_basic_block() 

826 

827 def get_size(self): 

828 builder = self.builder 

829 count = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, self.zero) 

830 # Sum all true values 

831 with cgutils.for_range(builder, self.size) as loop: 

832 c = builder.load(count) 

833 pred = _getitem_array_single_int( 

834 self.context, builder, self.idxty.dtype, 

835 self.idxty, self.idxary, loop.index 

836 ) 

837 c = builder.add(c, builder.zext(pred, c.type)) 

838 builder.store(c, count) 

839 

840 return builder.load(count) 

841 

842 def get_shape(self): 

843 return (self.get_size(),) 

844 

845 def get_index_bounds(self): 

846 # Pessimal heuristic, as we don't want to scan for the 

847 # first and last true items 

848 return (self.ll_intp(0), self.size) 

849 

850 def loop_head(self): 

851 builder = self.builder 

852 # Initialize loop variable 

853 self.builder.store(self.zero, self.idx_index) 

854 self.builder.store(self.zero, self.count) 

855 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

856 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_start) 

857 cur_index = builder.load(self.idx_index) 

858 cur_count = builder.load(self.count) 

859 with builder.if_then(builder.icmp_signed('>=', cur_index, self.size), 

860 likely=False): 

861 builder.branch(self.bb_end) 

862 # Load the predicate and branch if false 

863 pred = _getitem_array_single_int( 

864 self.context, builder, self.idxty.dtype, self.idxty, self.idxary, 

865 cur_index 

866 ) 

867 with builder.if_then(builder.not_(pred)): 

868 builder.branch(self.bb_tail) 

869 # Increment the count for next iteration 

870 next_count = cgutils.increment_index(builder, cur_count) 

871 builder.store(next_count, self.count) 

872 return cur_index, cur_count 

873 

874 def loop_tail(self): 

875 builder = self.builder 

876 builder.branch(self.bb_tail) 

877 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_tail) 

878 next_index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, 

879 builder.load(self.idx_index)) 

880 builder.store(next_index, self.idx_index) 

881 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

882 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_end)

885class SliceIndexer(Indexer): 

886 """ 

887 Compute indices along a slice. 

888 """ 

889 

890 def __init__(self, context, builder, aryty, ary, dim, idxty, slice): 

891 self.context = context 

892 self.builder = builder 

893 self.aryty = aryty 

894 self.ary = ary 

895 self.dim = dim 

896 self.idxty = idxty 

897 self.slice = slice 

898 self.ll_intp = self.context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

899 self.zero = Constant(self.ll_intp, 0) 

900 

901 def prepare(self): 

902 builder = self.builder 

903 # Fix slice for the dimension's size 

904 self.dim_size = builder.extract_value(self.ary.shape, self.dim) 

905 slicing.guard_invalid_slice(self.context, builder, self.idxty, 

906 self.slice) 

907 slicing.fix_slice(builder, self.slice, self.dim_size) 

908 self.is_step_negative = cgutils.is_neg_int(builder, self.slice.step) 

909 # Create loop entities 

910 self.index = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

911 self.count = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, self.ll_intp) 

912 self.bb_start = builder.append_basic_block() 

913 self.bb_end = builder.append_basic_block() 

914 

915 def get_size(self): 

916 return slicing.get_slice_length(self.builder, self.slice) 

917 

918 def get_shape(self): 

919 return (self.get_size(),) 

920 

921 def get_index_bounds(self): 

922 lower, upper = slicing.get_slice_bounds(self.builder, self.slice) 

923 return lower, upper 

924 

925 def loop_head(self): 

926 builder = self.builder 

927 # Initialize loop variable 

928 self.builder.store(self.slice.start, self.index) 

929 self.builder.store(self.zero, self.count) 

930 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

931 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_start) 

932 cur_index = builder.load(self.index) 

933 cur_count = builder.load(self.count) 

934 is_finished = builder.select(self.is_step_negative, 

935 builder.icmp_signed('<=', cur_index, 

936 self.slice.stop), 

937 builder.icmp_signed('>=', cur_index, 

938 self.slice.stop)) 

939 with builder.if_then(is_finished, likely=False): 

940 builder.branch(self.bb_end) 

941 return cur_index, cur_count 

942 

943 def loop_tail(self): 

944 builder = self.builder 

945 next_index = builder.add(builder.load(self.index), self.slice.step, 

946 flags=['nsw']) 

947 builder.store(next_index, self.index) 

948 next_count = cgutils.increment_index(builder, builder.load(self.count)) 

949 builder.store(next_count, self.count) 

950 builder.branch(self.bb_start) 

951 builder.position_at_end(self.bb_end)

954class FancyIndexer(object): 

955 """ 

956 Perform fancy indexing on the given array. 

957 """ 

958 

959 def __init__(self, context, builder, aryty, ary, index_types, indices): 

960 self.context = context 

961 self.builder = builder 

962 self.aryty = aryty 

963 self.shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape, aryty.ndim) 

964 self.strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides, aryty.ndim) 

965 self.ll_intp = self.context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

966 self.newaxes = [] 

967 

968 indexers = [] 

969 num_newaxes = len([idx for idx in index_types if is_nonelike(idx)]) 

970 

971 ax = 0 # keeps track of position of original axes 

972 new_ax = 0 # keeps track of position for inserting new axes 

973 for indexval, idxty in zip(indices, index_types): 

974 if idxty is types.ellipsis: 

975 # Fill up missing dimensions at the middle 

976 n_missing = aryty.ndim - len(indices) + 1 + num_newaxes 

977 for i in range(n_missing): 

978 indexer = EntireIndexer(context, builder, aryty, ary, ax) 

979 indexers.append(indexer) 

980 ax += 1 

981 new_ax += 1 

982 continue 

983 

984 # Regular index value 

985 if isinstance(idxty, types.SliceType): 

986 slice = context.make_helper(builder, idxty, indexval) 

987 indexer = SliceIndexer(context, builder, aryty, ary, ax, 

988 idxty, slice) 

989 indexers.append(indexer) 

990 elif isinstance(idxty, types.Integer): 

991 ind = fix_integer_index(context, builder, idxty, indexval, 

992 self.shapes[ax]) 

993 indexer = IntegerIndexer(context, builder, ind) 

994 indexers.append(indexer) 

995 elif isinstance(idxty, types.Array): 

996 idxary = make_array(idxty)(context, builder, indexval) 

997 if isinstance(idxty.dtype, types.Integer): 

998 indexer = IntegerArrayIndexer(context, builder, 

999 idxty, idxary, 

1000 self.shapes[ax]) 

1001 elif isinstance(idxty.dtype, types.Boolean): 

1002 indexer = BooleanArrayIndexer(context, builder, 

1003 idxty, idxary) 

1004 else: 

1005 assert 0 

1006 indexers.append(indexer) 

1007 elif is_nonelike(idxty): 

1008 self.newaxes.append(new_ax) 

1009 ax -= 1 

1010 else: 

1011 raise AssertionError("unexpected index type: %s" % (idxty,)) 

1012 ax += 1 

1013 new_ax += 1 

1014 

1015 # Fill up missing dimensions at the end 

1016 assert ax <= aryty.ndim, (ax, aryty.ndim) 

1017 while ax < aryty.ndim: 

1018 indexer = EntireIndexer(context, builder, aryty, ary, ax) 

1019 indexers.append(indexer) 

1020 ax += 1 

1021 

1022 assert len(indexers) == aryty.ndim, (len(indexers), aryty.ndim) 

1023 self.indexers = indexers 

1024 

1025 def prepare(self): 

1026 for i in self.indexers: 

1027 i.prepare() 

1028 

1029 one = self.context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

1030 

1031 # Compute the resulting shape given by the indices 

1032 res_shape = [i.get_shape() for i in self.indexers] 

1033 

1034 # At every position where newaxis/None is present insert 

1035 # one as a constant shape in the resulting list of shapes. 

1036 for i in self.newaxes: 

1037 res_shape.insert(i, (one,)) 

1038 

1039 # Store the shape as a tuple, we can't do a simple 

1040 # tuple(res_shape) here since res_shape is a list 

1041 # of tuples which may be differently sized. 

1042 self.indexers_shape = sum(res_shape, ()) 

1043 

1044 def get_shape(self): 

1045 """ 

1046 Get the resulting data shape as Python tuple. 

1047 """ 

1048 return self.indexers_shape 

1049 

1050 def get_offset_bounds(self, strides, itemsize): 

1051 """ 

1052 Get a half-open [lower, upper) range of byte offsets spanned by 

1053 the indexer with the given strides and itemsize. The indexer is 

1054 guaranteed to not go past those bounds. 

1055 """ 

1056 assert len(strides) == self.aryty.ndim 

1057 builder = self.builder 

1058 is_empty = cgutils.false_bit 

1059 zero = self.ll_intp(0) 

1060 one = self.ll_intp(1) 

1061 lower = zero 

1062 upper = zero 

1063 for indexer, shape, stride in zip(self.indexers, self.indexers_shape, 

1064 strides): 

1065 is_empty = builder.or_(is_empty, 

1066 builder.icmp_unsigned('==', shape, zero)) 

1067 # Compute [lower, upper) indices on this dimension 

1068 lower_index, upper_index = indexer.get_index_bounds() 

1069 lower_offset = builder.mul(stride, lower_index) 

1070 upper_offset = builder.mul(stride, builder.sub(upper_index, one)) 

1071 # Adjust total interval 

1072 is_downwards = builder.icmp_signed('<', stride, zero) 

1073 lower = builder.add(lower, 

1074 builder.select(is_downwards, 

1075 upper_offset, 

1076 lower_offset)) 

1077 upper = builder.add(upper, 

1078 builder.select(is_downwards, 

1079 lower_offset, 

1080 upper_offset)) 

1081 # Make interval half-open 

1082 upper = builder.add(upper, itemsize) 

1083 # Adjust for empty shape 

1084 lower = builder.select(is_empty, zero, lower) 

1085 upper = builder.select(is_empty, zero, upper) 

1086 return lower, upper 

1087 

1088 def begin_loops(self): 

1089 indices, counts = zip(*(i.loop_head() for i in self.indexers)) 

1090 return indices, counts 

1091 

1092 def end_loops(self): 

1093 for i in reversed(self.indexers): 

1094 i.loop_tail() 

1095

1097def fancy_getitem(context, builder, sig, args, 

1098 aryty, ary, index_types, indices): 

1099 

1100 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape) 

1101 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides) 

1102 data = ary.data 

1103 

1104 indexer = FancyIndexer(context, builder, aryty, ary, 

1105 index_types, indices) 

1106 indexer.prepare() 

1107 

1108 # Construct output array 

1109 out_ty = sig.return_type 

1110 out_shapes = indexer.get_shape() 

1111 

1112 out = _empty_nd_impl(context, builder, out_ty, out_shapes) 

1113 out_data = out.data 

1114 out_idx = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, 

1115 context.get_constant(types.intp, 0)) 

1116 

1117 # Loop on source and copy to destination 

1118 indices, _ = indexer.begin_loops() 

1119 

1120 # No need to check for wraparound, as the indexers all ensure 

1121 # a positive index is returned. 

1122 ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, data, shapes, strides, 

1123 aryty.layout, indices, wraparound=False, 

1124 boundscheck=context.enable_boundscheck) 

1125 val = load_item(context, builder, aryty, ptr) 

1126 

1127 # Since the destination is C-contiguous, no need for multi-dimensional 

1128 # indexing. 

1129 cur = builder.load(out_idx) 

1130 ptr = builder.gep(out_data, [cur]) 

1131 store_item(context, builder, out_ty, val, ptr) 

1132 next_idx = cgutils.increment_index(builder, cur) 

1133 builder.store(next_idx, out_idx) 

1134 

1135 indexer.end_loops() 

1136 

1137 return impl_ret_new_ref(context, builder, out_ty, out._getvalue())

1160def offset_bounds_from_strides(context, builder, arrty, arr, shapes, strides): 

1161 """ 

1162 Compute a half-open range [lower, upper) of byte offsets from the 

1163 array's data pointer, that bound the in-memory extent of the array. 

1164 

1165 This mimics offset_bounds_from_strides() from 

1166 numpy/core/src/private/mem_overlap.c 

1167 """ 

1168 itemsize = arr.itemsize 

1169 zero = itemsize.type(0) 

1170 one = zero.type(1) 

1171 if arrty.layout in 'CF': 

1172 # Array is contiguous: contents are laid out sequentially 

1173 # starting from arr.data and upwards 

1174 lower = zero 

1175 upper = builder.mul(itemsize, arr.nitems) 

1176 else: 

1177 # Non-contiguous array: need to examine strides 

1178 lower = zero 

1179 upper = zero 

1180 for i in range(arrty.ndim): 

1181 # Compute the largest byte offset on this dimension 

1182 # max_axis_offset = strides[i] * (shapes[i] - 1) 

1183 # (shapes[i] == 0 is catered for by the empty array case below) 

1184 max_axis_offset = builder.mul(strides[i], 

1185 builder.sub(shapes[i], one)) 

1186 is_upwards = builder.icmp_signed('>=', max_axis_offset, zero) 

1187 # Expand either upwards or downwards depending on stride 

1188 upper = builder.select(is_upwards, 

1189 builder.add(upper, max_axis_offset), upper) 

1190 lower = builder.select(is_upwards, 

1191 lower, builder.add(lower, max_axis_offset)) 

1192 # Return a half-open range 

1193 upper = builder.add(upper, itemsize) 

1194 # Adjust for empty arrays 

1195 is_empty = builder.icmp_signed('==', arr.nitems, zero) 

1196 upper = builder.select(is_empty, zero, upper) 

1197 lower = builder.select(is_empty, zero, lower) 

1198 

1199 return lower, upper

1202def compute_memory_extents(context, builder, lower, upper, data): 

1203 """ 

1204 Given [lower, upper) byte offsets and a base data pointer, 

1205 compute the memory pointer bounds as pointer-sized integers. 

1206 """ 

1207 data_ptr_as_int = builder.ptrtoint(data, lower.type) 

1208 start = builder.add(data_ptr_as_int, lower) 

1209 end = builder.add(data_ptr_as_int, upper) 

1210 return start, end

1213def get_array_memory_extents(context, builder, arrty, arr, shapes, strides, 

1214 data): 

1215 """ 

1216 Compute a half-open range [start, end) of pointer-sized integers 

1217 which fully contain the array data. 

1218 """ 

1219 lower, upper = offset_bounds_from_strides(context, builder, arrty, arr, 

1220 shapes, strides) 

1221 return compute_memory_extents(context, builder, lower, upper, data)

1224def extents_may_overlap(context, builder, a_start, a_end, b_start, b_end): 

1225 """ 

1226 Whether two memory extents [a_start, a_end) and [b_start, b_end) 

1227 may overlap. 

1228 """ 

1229 # Comparisons are unsigned, since we are really comparing pointers 

1230 may_overlap = builder.and_( 

1231 builder.icmp_unsigned('<', a_start, b_end), 

1232 builder.icmp_unsigned('<', b_start, a_end), 

1233 ) 

1234 return may_overlap

1242 copy_data = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, src_data) 

1243 copy_shapes = src_shapes 

1244 copy_strides = None # unneeded for contiguous arrays 

1245 

1246 with builder.if_then(use_copy, likely=False): 

1247 # Allocate temporary scratchpad 

1248 # XXX: should we use a stack-allocated array for very small 

1249 # data sizes? 

1250 allocsize = builder.mul(src.itemsize, src.nitems) 

1251 data = context.nrt.allocate(builder, allocsize) 

1252 voidptrty = data.type 

1253 data = builder.bitcast(data, ptrty) 

1254 builder.store(data, copy_data) 

1255 

1256 # Copy source data into scratchpad 

1257 intp_t = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

1258 

1259 with cgutils.loop_nest(builder, src_shapes, intp_t) as indices: 

1260 src_ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, src_data, 

1261 src_shapes, src_strides, 

1262 srcty.layout, indices) 

1263 dest_ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, data, 

1264 copy_shapes, copy_strides, 

1265 copy_layout, indices) 

1266 builder.store(builder.load(src_ptr), dest_ptr) 

1267 

1268 def src_getitem(source_indices): 

1269 src_ptr = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ptrty) 

1270 with builder.if_else(use_copy, likely=False) as (if_copy, otherwise): 

1271 with if_copy: 

1272 builder.store( 

1273 cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, 

1274 builder.load(copy_data), 

1275 copy_shapes, copy_strides, 

1276 copy_layout, source_indices, 

1277 wraparound=False), 

1278 src_ptr) 

1279 with otherwise: 

1280 builder.store( 

1281 cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, src_data, 

1282 src_shapes, src_strides, 

1283 srcty.layout, source_indices, 

1284 wraparound=False), 

1285 src_ptr) 

1286 return load_item(context, builder, srcty, builder.load(src_ptr)) 

1287 

1288 def src_cleanup(): 

1289 # Deallocate memory 

1290 with builder.if_then(use_copy, likely=False): 

1291 data = builder.load(copy_data) 

1292 data = builder.bitcast(data, voidptrty) 

1293 context.nrt.free(builder, data) 

1294 

1295 return src_getitem, src_cleanup

1298def _bc_adjust_dimension(context, builder, shapes, strides, target_shape): 

1299 """ 

1300 Preprocess dimension for broadcasting. 

1301 Returns (shapes, strides) such that the ndim match *target_shape*. 

1302 When expanding to higher ndim, the returning shapes and strides are 

1303 prepended with ones and zeros, respectively. 

1304 When truncating to lower ndim, the shapes are checked (in runtime). 

1305 All extra dimension must have size of 1. 

1306 """ 

1307 zero = context.get_constant(types.uintp, 0) 

1308 one = context.get_constant(types.uintp, 1) 

1309 

1310 # Adjust for broadcasting to higher dimension 

1311 if len(target_shape) > len(shapes): 

1312 nd_diff = len(target_shape) - len(shapes) 

1313 # Fill missing shapes with one, strides with zeros 

1314 shapes = [one] * nd_diff + shapes 

1315 strides = [zero] * nd_diff + strides 

1316 # Adjust for broadcasting to lower dimension 

1317 elif len(target_shape) < len(shapes): 

1318 # Accepted if all extra dims has shape 1 

1319 nd_diff = len(shapes) - len(target_shape) 

1320 dim_is_one = [builder.icmp_unsigned('==', sh, one) 

1321 for sh in shapes[:nd_diff]] 

1322 accepted = functools.reduce(builder.and_, dim_is_one, 

1323 cgutils.true_bit) 

1324 # Check error 

1325 with builder.if_then(builder.not_(accepted), likely=False): 

1326 msg = "cannot broadcast source array for assignment" 

1327 context.call_conv.return_user_exc(builder, ValueError, (msg,)) 

1328 # Truncate extra shapes, strides 

1329 shapes = shapes[nd_diff:] 

1330 strides = strides[nd_diff:] 

1331 

1332 return shapes, strides 

1333 

1334 

1335def _bc_adjust_shape_strides(context, builder, shapes, strides, target_shape): 

1336 """ 

1337 Broadcast shapes and strides to target_shape given that their ndim already 

1338 matches. For each location where the shape is 1 and does not match the 

1339 dim for target, it is set to the value at the target and the stride is 

1340 set to zero. 

1341 """ 

1342 bc_shapes = [] 

1343 bc_strides = [] 

1344 zero = context.get_constant(types.uintp, 0) 

1345 one = context.get_constant(types.uintp, 1) 

1346 # Adjust all mismatching ones in shape 

1347 mismatch = [builder.icmp_signed('!=', tar, old) 

1348 for tar, old in zip(target_shape, shapes)] 

1349 src_is_one = [builder.icmp_signed('==', old, one) for old in shapes] 

1350 preds = [builder.and_(x, y) for x, y in zip(mismatch, src_is_one)] 

1351 bc_shapes = [builder.select(p, tar, old) 

1352 for p, tar, old in zip(preds, target_shape, shapes)] 

1353 bc_strides = [builder.select(p, zero, old) 

1354 for p, old in zip(preds, strides)] 

1355 return bc_shapes, bc_strides 

1356 

1357 

1358def _broadcast_to_shape(context, builder, arrtype, arr, target_shape): 

1359 """ 

1360 Broadcast the given array to the target_shape. 

1361 Returns (array_type, array) 

1362 """ 

1363 # Compute broadcasted shape and strides 

1364 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape) 

1365 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.strides) 

1366 

1367 shapes, strides = _bc_adjust_dimension(context, builder, shapes, strides, 

1368 target_shape) 

1369 shapes, strides = _bc_adjust_shape_strides(context, builder, shapes, 

1370 strides, target_shape) 

1371 new_arrtype = arrtype.copy(ndim=len(target_shape), layout='A') 

1372 # Create new view 

1373 new_arr = make_array(new_arrtype)(context, builder) 

1374 populate_array(new_arr, 

1375 data=arr.data, 

1376 shape=cgutils.pack_array(builder, shapes), 

1377 strides=cgutils.pack_array(builder, strides), 

1378 itemsize=arr.itemsize, 

1379 meminfo=arr.meminfo, 

1380 parent=arr.parent) 

1381 return new_arrtype, new_arr

1425@register_jitable 

1426def _can_broadcast(array, dest_shape): 

1427 src_shape = array.shape 

1428 src_ndim = len(src_shape) 

1429 dest_ndim = len(dest_shape) 

1430 if src_ndim > dest_ndim: 

1431 raise ValueError('input operand has more dimensions than allowed ' 

1432 'by the axis remapping') 

1433 for size in dest_shape: 

1434 if size < 0: 

1435 raise ValueError('all elements of broadcast shape must be ' 

1436 'non-negative') 

1437 

1438 # based on _broadcast_onto function in numba/np/npyimpl.py 

1439 src_index = 0 

1440 dest_index = dest_ndim - src_ndim 

1441 while src_index < src_ndim: 

1442 src_dim = src_shape[src_index] 

1443 dest_dim = dest_shape[dest_index] 

1444 # possible cases for (src_dim, dest_dim): 

1445 # * (1, 1) -> Ok 

1446 # * (>1, 1) -> Error! 

1447 # * (>1, >1) -> src_dim == dest_dim else error! 

1448 # * (1, >1) -> Ok 

1449 if src_dim == dest_dim or src_dim == 1: 

1450 src_index += 1 

1451 dest_index += 1 

1452 else: 

1453 raise ValueError('operands could not be broadcast together ' 

1454 'with remapped shapes') 

1455

1457def _default_broadcast_to_impl(array, shape): 

1458 array = np.asarray(array) 

1459 _can_broadcast(array, shape) 

1460 return _numpy_broadcast_to(array, shape)

1463@overload(np.broadcast_to) 

1464def numpy_broadcast_to(array, shape): 

1465 if not type_can_asarray(array): 

1466 raise errors.TypingError('The first argument "array" must ' 

1467 'be array-like') 

1468 

1469 if isinstance(shape, types.Integer): 

1470 def impl(array, shape): 

1471 return np.broadcast_to(array, (shape,)) 

1472 return impl 

1473 

1474 elif isinstance(shape, types.UniTuple): 

1475 if not isinstance(shape.dtype, types.Integer): 

1476 msg = 'The second argument "shape" must be a tuple of integers' 

1477 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

1478 return _default_broadcast_to_impl 

1479 

1480 elif isinstance(shape, types.Tuple) and shape.count > 0: 

1481 # check if all types are integers 

1482 if not all([isinstance(typ, types.IntegerLiteral) for typ in shape]): 

1483 msg = f'"{shape}" object cannot be interpreted as an integer' 

1484 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

1485 return _default_broadcast_to_impl 

1486 elif isinstance(shape, types.Tuple) and shape.count == 0: 

1487 is_scalar_array = isinstance(array, types.Array) and array.ndim == 0 

1488 if type_is_scalar(array) or is_scalar_array: 

1489 

1490 def impl(array, shape): # broadcast_to(array, ()) 

1491 # Array type must be supported by "type_can_asarray" 

1492 # Quick note that unicode types are not supported! 

1493 array = np.asarray(array) 

1494 return get_readonly_array(array) 

1495 return impl 

1496 

1497 else: 

1498 msg = 'Cannot broadcast a non-scalar to a scalar array' 

1499 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

1500 else: 

1501 msg = ('The argument "shape" must be a tuple or an integer. ' 

1502 'Got %s' % shape) 

1503 raise errors.TypingError(msg)

1506@register_jitable 

1507def numpy_broadcast_shapes_list(r, m, shape): 

1508 for i in range(len(shape)): 

1509 k = m - len(shape) + i 

1510 tmp = shape[i] 

1511 if tmp < 0: 

1512 raise ValueError("negative dimensions are not allowed") 

1513 if tmp == 1: 

1514 continue 

1515 if r[k] == 1: 

1516 r[k] = tmp 

1517 elif r[k] != tmp: 

1518 raise ValueError("shape mismatch: objects" 

1519 " cannot be broadcast" 

1520 " to a single shape")

1523@overload(np.broadcast_shapes) 

1524def ol_numpy_broadcast_shapes(*args): 

1525 # Based on https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/f702b26fff3271ba6a6ba29a021fc19051d1f007/numpy/core/src/multiarray/iterators.c#L1129-L1212 # noqa 

1526 for idx, arg in enumerate(args): 

1527 is_int = isinstance(arg, types.Integer) 

1528 is_int_tuple = isinstance(arg, types.UniTuple) and \ 

1529 isinstance(arg.dtype, types.Integer) 

1530 is_empty_tuple = isinstance(arg, types.Tuple) and len(arg.types) == 0 

1531 if not (is_int or is_int_tuple or is_empty_tuple): 

1532 msg = (f'Argument {idx} must be either an int or tuple[int]. ' 

1533 f'Got {arg}') 

1534 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

1535 

1536 # discover the number of dimensions 

1537 m = 0 

1538 for arg in args: 

1539 if isinstance(arg, types.Integer): 

1540 m = max(m, 1) 

1541 elif isinstance(arg, types.BaseTuple): 

1542 m = max(m, len(arg)) 

1543 

1544 if m == 0: 

1545 return lambda *args: () 

1546 else: 

1547 tup_init = (1,) * m 

1548 

1549 def impl(*args): 

1550 # propagate args 

1551 r = [1] * m 

1552 tup = tup_init 

1553 for arg in literal_unroll(args): 

1554 if isinstance(arg, tuple) and len(arg) > 0: 

1555 numpy_broadcast_shapes_list(r, m, arg) 

1556 elif isinstance(arg, int): 

1557 numpy_broadcast_shapes_list(r, m, (arg,)) 

1558 for idx, elem in enumerate(r): 

1559 tup = tuple_setitem(tup, idx, elem) 

1560 return tup 

1561 return impl

1564@overload(np.broadcast_arrays) 

1565def numpy_broadcast_arrays(*args): 

1566 

1567 for idx, arg in enumerate(args): 

1568 if not type_can_asarray(arg): 

1569 raise errors.TypingError(f'Argument "{idx}" must ' 

1570 'be array-like') 

1571 

1572 unified_dtype = None 

1573 dt = None 

1574 for arg in args: 

1575 if isinstance(arg, (types.Array, types.BaseTuple)): 

1576 dt = arg.dtype 

1577 else: 

1578 dt = arg 

1579 

1580 if unified_dtype is None: 

1581 unified_dtype = dt 

1582 elif unified_dtype != dt: 

1583 raise errors.TypingError('Mismatch of argument types. Numba cannot ' 

1584 'broadcast arrays with different types. ' 

1585 f'Got {args}') 

1586 

1587 # number of dimensions 

1588 m = 0 

1589 for idx, arg in enumerate(args): 

1590 if isinstance(arg, types.ArrayCompatible): 

1591 m = max(m, arg.ndim) 

1592 elif isinstance(arg, (types.Number, types.Boolean, types.BaseTuple)): 

1593 m = max(m, 1) 

1594 else: 

1595 raise errors.TypingError(f'Unhandled type {arg}') 

1596 

1597 tup_init = (0,) * m 

1598 

1599 def impl(*args): 

1600 # find out the output shape 

1601 # we can't call np.broadcast_shapes here since args may have arrays 

1602 # with different shapes and it is not possible to create a list 

1603 # with those shapes dynamically 

1604 shape = [1] * m 

1605 for array in literal_unroll(args): 

1606 numpy_broadcast_shapes_list(shape, m, np.asarray(array).shape) 

1607 

1608 tup = tup_init 

1609 

1610 for i in range(m): 

1611 tup = tuple_setitem(tup, i, shape[i]) 

1612 

1613 # numpy checks if the input arrays have the same shape as `shape` 

1614 outs = [] 

1615 for array in literal_unroll(args): 

1616 outs.append(np.broadcast_to(np.asarray(array), tup)) 

1617 return outs 

1618 

1619 return impl

1622def fancy_setslice(context, builder, sig, args, index_types, indices): 

1623 """ 

1624 Implement slice assignment for arrays. This implementation works for 

1625 basic as well as fancy indexing, since there's no functional difference 

1626 between the two for indexed assignment. 

1627 """ 

1628 aryty, _, srcty = sig.args 

1629 ary, _, src = args 

1630 

1631 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, ary) 

1632 dest_shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.shape) 

1633 dest_strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides) 

1634 dest_data = ary.data 

1635 

1636 indexer = FancyIndexer(context, builder, aryty, ary, 

1637 index_types, indices) 

1638 indexer.prepare() 

1639 

1640 if isinstance(srcty, types.Buffer): 

1641 # Source is an array 

1642 src_dtype = srcty.dtype 

1643 index_shape = indexer.get_shape() 

1644 src = make_array(srcty)(context, builder, src) 

1645 # Broadcast source array to shape 

1646 srcty, src = _broadcast_to_shape(context, builder, srcty, src, 

1647 index_shape) 

1648 src_shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, src.shape) 

1649 src_strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, src.strides) 

1650 src_data = src.data 

1651 

1652 # Check shapes are equal 

1653 shape_error = cgutils.false_bit 

1654 assert len(index_shape) == len(src_shapes) 

1655 

1656 for u, v in zip(src_shapes, index_shape): 

1657 shape_error = builder.or_(shape_error, 

1658 builder.icmp_signed('!=', u, v)) 

1659 

1660 with builder.if_then(shape_error, likely=False): 

1661 def raise_impl(src_shapes, index_shape): 

1662 return ("cannot assign slice of shape " + 

1663 f"({', '.join([str(x) for x in src_shapes])}) from " + 

1664 "input of shape " + 

1665 f"({', '.join([str(x) for x in index_shape])})") 

1666 

1667 sig = types.unicode_type( 

1668 types.UniTuple(types.int64, len(src_shapes)), 

1669 types.UniTuple(types.int64, len(index_shape))) 

1670 tup = (context.make_tuple(builder, sig.args[0], src_shapes), 

1671 context.make_tuple(builder, sig.args[1], index_shape)) 

1672 

1673 res = context.compile_internal(builder, raise_impl, sig, tup) 

1674 msg = impl_ret_new_ref(context, builder, sig, res) 

1675 context.call_conv.return_dynamic_user_exc(builder, ValueError, 

1676 (msg,), 

1677 (types.unicode_type,)) 

1678 

1679 # Check for array overlap 

1680 src_start, src_end = get_array_memory_extents(context, builder, srcty, 

1681 src, src_shapes, 

1682 src_strides, src_data) 

1683 

1684 dest_lower, dest_upper = indexer.get_offset_bounds(dest_strides, 

1685 ary.itemsize) 

1686 dest_start, dest_end = compute_memory_extents(context, builder, 

1687 dest_lower, dest_upper, 

1688 dest_data) 

1689 

1690 use_copy = extents_may_overlap(context, builder, src_start, src_end, 

1691 dest_start, dest_end) 

1692 

1693 src_getitem, src_cleanup = maybe_copy_source(context, builder, use_copy, 

1694 srcty, src, src_shapes, 

1695 src_strides, src_data) 

1696 

1697 elif isinstance(srcty, types.Sequence): 

1698 src_dtype = srcty.dtype 

1699 

1700 # Check shape is equal to sequence length 

1701 index_shape = indexer.get_shape() 

1702 assert len(index_shape) == 1 

1703 len_impl = context.get_function(len, signature(types.intp, srcty)) 

1704 seq_len = len_impl(builder, (src,)) 

1705 

1706 shape_error = builder.icmp_signed('!=', index_shape[0], seq_len) 

1707 

1708 with builder.if_then(shape_error, likely=False): 

1709 def raise_impl(seq_len, input_shape): 

1710 return (f"cannot assign slice of shape ({seq_len}, )" + 

1711 f"from input of shape ({input_shape}, )") 

1712 

1713 tup = (seq_len, index_shape[0]) 

1714 sig = types.unicode_type(types.int64, types.int64) 

1715 res = context.compile_internal(builder, raise_impl, sig, tup) 

1716 msg = impl_ret_new_ref(context, builder, sig, res) 

1717 context.call_conv.return_dynamic_user_exc(builder, ValueError, 

1718 (msg,), 

1719 (types.unicode_type,)) 

1720 

1721 def src_getitem(source_indices): 

1722 idx, = source_indices 

1723 getitem_impl = context.get_function( 

1724 operator.getitem, 

1725 signature(src_dtype, srcty, types.intp), 

1726 ) 

1727 return getitem_impl(builder, (src, idx)) 

1728 

1729 def src_cleanup(): 

1730 pass 

1731 

1732 else: 

1733 # Source is a scalar (broadcast or not, depending on destination 

1734 # shape). 

1735 src_dtype = srcty 

1736 

1737 def src_getitem(source_indices): 

1738 return src 

1739 

1740 def src_cleanup(): 

1741 pass 

1742 

1743 zero = context.get_constant(types.uintp, 0) 

1744 # Loop on destination and copy from source to destination 

1745 dest_indices, counts = indexer.begin_loops() 

1746 

1747 # Source is iterated in natural order 

1748 

1749 # Counts represent a counter for the number of times a specified axis 

1750 # is being accessed, during setitem they are used as source 

1751 # indices 

1752 counts = list(counts) 

1753 

1754 # We need to artifically introduce the index zero wherever a 

1755 # newaxis is present within the indexer. These always remain 

1756 # zero. 

1757 for i in indexer.newaxes: 

1758 counts.insert(i, zero) 

1759 

1760 source_indices = [c for c in counts if c is not None] 

1761 

1762 val = src_getitem(source_indices) 

1763 

1764 # Cast to the destination dtype (cross-dtype slice assignment is allowed) 

1765 val = context.cast(builder, val, src_dtype, aryty.dtype) 

1766 

1767 # No need to check for wraparound, as the indexers all ensure 

1768 # a positive index is returned. 

1769 dest_ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, dest_data, 

1770 dest_shapes, dest_strides, 

1771 aryty.layout, dest_indices, 

1772 wraparound=False, 

1773 boundscheck=context.enable_boundscheck) 

1774 store_item(context, builder, aryty, val, dest_ptr) 

1775 

1776 indexer.end_loops() 

1777 

1778 src_cleanup() 

1779 

1780 return context.get_dummy_value()

1786def vararg_to_tuple(context, builder, sig, args): 

1787 aryty = sig.args[0] 

1788 dimtys = sig.args[1:] 

1789 # values 

1790 ary = args[0] 

1791 dims = args[1:] 

1792 # coerce all types to intp 

1793 dims = [context.cast(builder, val, ty, types.intp) 

1794 for ty, val in zip(dimtys, dims)] 

1795 # make a tuple 

1796 shape = cgutils.pack_array(builder, dims, dims[0].type) 

1797 

1798 shapety = types.UniTuple(dtype=types.intp, count=len(dims)) 

1799 new_sig = typing.signature(sig.return_type, aryty, shapety) 

1800 new_args = ary, shape 

1801 

1802 return new_sig, new_args

1810def permute_arrays(axis, shape, strides): 

1811 if len(axis) != len(set(axis)): 

1812 raise ValueError("repeated axis in transpose") 

1813 dim = len(shape) 

1814 for x in axis: 

1815 if x >= dim or abs(x) > dim: 

1816 raise ValueError("axis is out of bounds for array of " 

1817 "given dimension") 

1818 

1819 shape[:] = shape[axis]

2041def _attempt_nocopy_reshape(context, builder, aryty, ary, 

2042 newnd, newshape, newstrides): 

2043 """ 

2044 Call into Numba_attempt_nocopy_reshape() for the given array type 

2045 and instance, and the specified new shape. 

2046 

2047 Return value is non-zero if successful, and the array pointed to 

2048 by *newstrides* will be filled up with the computed results. 

2049 """ 

2050 ll_intp = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

2051 ll_intp_star = ll_intp.as_pointer() 

2052 ll_intc = context.get_value_type(types.intc) 

2053 fnty = ir.FunctionType(ll_intc, [ 

2054 # nd, *dims, *strides 

2055 ll_intp, ll_intp_star, ll_intp_star, 

2056 # newnd, *newdims, *newstrides 

2057 ll_intp, ll_intp_star, ll_intp_star, 

2058 # itemsize, is_f_order 

2059 ll_intp, ll_intc]) 

2060 fn = cgutils.get_or_insert_function(builder.module, fnty, 

2061 "numba_attempt_nocopy_reshape") 

2062 

2063 nd = ll_intp(aryty.ndim) 

2064 shape = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, ary._get_ptr_by_name('shape'), 0, 0) 

2065 strides = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, ary._get_ptr_by_name('strides'), 

2066 0, 0) 

2067 newnd = ll_intp(newnd) 

2068 newshape = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, newshape, 0, 0) 

2069 newstrides = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, newstrides, 0, 0) 

2070 is_f_order = ll_intc(0) 

2071 res = builder.call(fn, [nd, shape, strides, 

2072 newnd, newshape, newstrides, 

2073 ary.itemsize, is_f_order])

2077def normalize_reshape_value(origsize, shape): 

2078 num_neg_value = 0 

2079 known_size = 1 

2080 for ax, s in enumerate(shape): 

2081 if s < 0: 

2082 num_neg_value += 1 

2083 neg_ax = ax 

2084 else: 

2085 known_size *= s 

2086 

2087 if num_neg_value == 0: 

2088 if origsize != known_size: 

2089 raise ValueError("total size of new array must be unchanged") 

2090 

2091 elif num_neg_value == 1: 

2092 # Infer negative dimension 

2093 if known_size == 0: 

2094 inferred = 0 

2095 ok = origsize == 0 

2096 else: 

2097 inferred = origsize // known_size 

2098 ok = origsize % known_size == 0 

2099 if not ok: 

2100 raise ValueError("total size of new array must be unchanged") 

2101 shape[neg_ax] = inferred 

2102 

2103 else: 

2104 raise ValueError("multiple negative shape values")

2397 # broadcast it to shape of a 

2398 # by using np.full_like 

2399 a_min_full = np.full_like(a, a_min) 

2400 return _np_clip_impl(a, a_min_full, a_max, out) 

2401 

2402 return np_clip_sa 

2403 elif not a_min_is_scalar and a_max_is_scalar: 

2404 if a_min_is_none: 

2405 def np_clip_ns(a, a_min, a_max, out=None): 

2406 # a_max is a scalar 

2407 # since its shape will be empty 

2408 # so broadcasting is not needed at all 

2409 ret = np.empty_like(a) if out is None else out 

2410 for index in np.ndindex(a.shape): 

2411 val_a = a[index] 

2412 ret[index] = min(val_a, a_max) 

2413 

2414 return ret 

2415 

2416 return np_clip_ns 

2417 else: 

2418 def np_clip_as(a, a_min, a_max, out=None): 

2419 # a_max is a scalar 

2420 # since its shape will be empty 

2421 # broadcast it to shape of a 

2422 # by using np.full_like 

2423 a_max_full = np.full_like(a, a_max) 

2424 return _np_clip_impl(a, a_min, a_max_full, out) 

2425 

2426 return np_clip_as 

2427 else: 

2428 # Case where exactly one of a_min or a_max is None 

2429 if a_min_is_none: 

2430 def np_clip_na(a, a_min, a_max, out=None): 

2431 # a_max is a numpy array but a_min is None 

2432 ret = np.empty_like(a) if out is None else out 

2433 a_b, a_max_b = np.broadcast_arrays(a, a_max) 

2434 return _np_clip_impl_none(a_b, a_max_b, True, ret) 

2435 

2436 return np_clip_na 

2437 elif a_max_is_none: 

2438 def np_clip_an(a, a_min, a_max, out=None): 

2439 # a_min is a numpy array but a_max is None 

2440 ret = np.empty_like(a) if out is None else out 

2441 a_b, a_min_b = np.broadcast_arrays(a, a_min) 

2442 return _np_clip_impl_none(a_b, a_min_b, False, ret) 

2443 

2444 return np_clip_an 

2445 else: 

2446 def np_clip_aa(a, a_min, a_max, out=None): 

2447 # Both a_min and a_max are clearly arrays 

2448 # because none of the above branches 

2449 # returned 

2450 return _np_clip_impl(a, a_min, a_max, out) 

2451 

2452 return np_clip_aa 

2453

2462def _change_dtype(context, builder, oldty, newty, ary): 

2463 """ 

2464 Attempt to fix up *ary* for switching from *oldty* to *newty*. 

2465 

2466 See Numpy's array_descr_set() 

2467 (np/core/src/multiarray/getset.c). 

2468 Attempt to fix the array's shape and strides for a new dtype. 

2469 False is returned on failure, True on success. 

2470 """ 

2471 assert oldty.ndim == newty.ndim 

2472 assert oldty.layout == newty.layout 

2473 

2474 new_layout = ord(newty.layout) 

2475 any_layout = ord('A') 

2476 c_layout = ord('C') 

2477 f_layout = ord('F') 

2478 

2479 int8 = types.int8 

2480 

2481 def imp(nd, dims, strides, old_itemsize, new_itemsize, layout): 

2482 # Attempt to update the layout due to limitation of the numba 

2483 # type system. 

2484 if layout == any_layout: 

2485 # Test rightmost stride to be contiguous 

2486 if strides[-1] == old_itemsize: 

2487 # Process this as if it is C contiguous 

2488 layout = int8(c_layout) 

2489 # Test leftmost stride to be F contiguous 

2490 elif strides[0] == old_itemsize: 

2491 # Process this as if it is F contiguous 

2492 layout = int8(f_layout) 

2493 

2494 if old_itemsize != new_itemsize and (layout == any_layout or nd == 0): 

2495 return False 

2496 

2497 if layout == c_layout: 

2498 i = nd - 1 

2499 else: 

2500 i = 0 

2501 

2502 if new_itemsize < old_itemsize: 

2503 # If it is compatible, increase the size of the dimension 

2504 # at the end (or at the front if F-contiguous) 

2505 if (old_itemsize % new_itemsize) != 0: 

2506 return False 

2507 

2508 newdim = old_itemsize // new_itemsize 

2509 dims[i] *= newdim 

2510 strides[i] = new_itemsize 

2511 

2512 elif new_itemsize > old_itemsize: 

2513 # Determine if last (or first if F-contiguous) dimension 

2514 # is compatible 

2515 bytelength = dims[i] * old_itemsize 

2516 if (bytelength % new_itemsize) != 0: 

2517 return False 

2518 

2519 dims[i] = bytelength // new_itemsize 

2520 strides[i] = new_itemsize 

2521 

2522 else: 

2523 # Same item size: nothing to do (this also works for 

2524 # non-contiguous arrays). 

2525 pass 

2526 

2527 return True 

2528 

2529 old_itemsize = context.get_constant(types.intp, 

2530 get_itemsize(context, oldty)) 

2531 new_itemsize = context.get_constant(types.intp, 

2532 get_itemsize(context, newty)) 

2533 

2534 nd = context.get_constant(types.intp, newty.ndim) 

2535 shape_data = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, ary._get_ptr_by_name('shape'), 

2536 0, 0) 

2537 strides_data = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

2538 ary._get_ptr_by_name('strides'), 0, 0) 

2539 

2540 shape_strides_array_type = types.Array(dtype=types.intp, ndim=1, layout='C') 

2541 arycls = context.make_array(shape_strides_array_type) 

2542 

2543 shape_constant = cgutils.pack_array(builder, 

2544 [context.get_constant(types.intp, 

2545 newty.ndim)]) 

2546 

2547 sizeof_intp = context.get_abi_sizeof(context.get_data_type(types.intp)) 

2548 sizeof_intp = context.get_constant(types.intp, sizeof_intp) 

2549 strides_constant = cgutils.pack_array(builder, [sizeof_intp]) 

2550 

2551 shape_ary = arycls(context, builder) 

2552 

2553 populate_array(shape_ary, 

2554 data=shape_data, 

2555 shape=shape_constant, 

2556 strides=strides_constant, 

2557 itemsize=sizeof_intp, 

2558 meminfo=None) 

2559 

2560 strides_ary = arycls(context, builder) 

2561 populate_array(strides_ary, 

2562 data=strides_data, 

2563 shape=shape_constant, 

2564 strides=strides_constant, 

2565 itemsize=sizeof_intp, 

2566 meminfo=None) 

2567 

2568 shape = shape_ary._getvalue() 

2569 strides = strides_ary._getvalue() 

2570 args = [nd, shape, strides, old_itemsize, new_itemsize, 

2571 context.get_constant(types.int8, new_layout)] 

2572 

2573 sig = signature(types.boolean, 

2574 types.intp, # nd 

2575 shape_strides_array_type, # dims 

2576 shape_strides_array_type, # strides 

2577 types.intp, # old_itemsize 

2578 types.intp, # new_itemsize 

2579 types.int8, # layout 

2580 ) 

2581 

2582 res = context.compile_internal(builder, imp, sig, args) 

2583 update_array_info(newty, ary) 

2584 res = impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, sig.return_type, res) 

2585 return res

2620@overload(np.repeat) 

2621def np_repeat(a, repeats): 

2622 # Implementation for repeats being a scalar is a module global function 

2623 # (see below) because it might be called from the implementation below. 

2624 

2625 def np_repeat_impl_repeats_array_like(a, repeats): 

2626 # implementation if repeats is an array like 

2627 repeats_array = np.asarray(repeats, dtype=np.int64) 

2628 # if it is a singleton array, invoke the scalar implementation 

2629 if repeats_array.shape[0] == 1: 

2630 return np_repeat_impl_repeats_scaler(a, repeats_array[0]) 

2631 if np.any(repeats_array < 0): 

2632 raise ValueError("negative dimensions are not allowed") 

2633 asa = np.asarray(a) 

2634 aravel = asa.ravel() 

2635 n = aravel.shape[0] 

2636 if aravel.shape != repeats_array.shape: 

2637 raise ValueError( 

2638 "operands could not be broadcast together") 

2639 to_return = np.empty(np.sum(repeats_array), dtype=asa.dtype) 

2640 pos = 0 

2641 for i in range(n): 

2642 to_return[pos : pos + repeats_array[i]] = aravel[i] 

2643 pos += repeats_array[i] 

2644 return to_return 

2645 

2646 # type checking 

2647 if isinstance(a, (types.Array, 

2648 types.List, 

2649 types.BaseTuple, 

2650 types.Number, 

2651 types.Boolean, 

2652 ) 

2653 ): 

2654 if isinstance(repeats, types.Integer): 

2655 return np_repeat_impl_repeats_scaler 

2656 elif isinstance(repeats, (types.Array, types.List)): 

2657 if isinstance(repeats.dtype, types.Integer): 

2658 return np_repeat_impl_repeats_array_like 

2659 

2660 raise errors.TypingError( 

2661 "The repeats argument must be an integer " 

2662 "or an array-like of integer dtype") 

2663 

2664 

2665@register_jitable 

2666def np_repeat_impl_repeats_scaler(a, repeats): 

2667 if repeats < 0: 

2668 raise ValueError("negative dimensions are not allowed") 

2669 asa = np.asarray(a) 

2670 aravel = asa.ravel() 

2671 n = aravel.shape[0] 

2672 if repeats == 0: 

2673 return np.empty(0, dtype=asa.dtype) 

2674 elif repeats == 1: 

2675 return np.copy(aravel) 

2676 else: 

2677 to_return = np.empty(n * repeats, dtype=asa.dtype) 

2678 for i in range(n): 

2679 to_return[i * repeats : (i + 1) * repeats] = aravel[i] 

2680 return to_return

2694 sig = types.intp(dtype)

2696 def codegen(cgctx, builder, sig, llargs):

2703def _compatible_view(a, dtype): 

2704 pass 

2705 

2706 

2707@overload(_compatible_view, target='generic') 

2708def ol_compatible_view(a, dtype): 

2709 """Determines if the array and dtype are compatible for forming a view.""" 

2710 # NOTE: NumPy 1.23+ uses this check. 

2711 # Code based on: 

2712 # https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/750ad21258cfc00663586d5a466e24f91b48edc7/numpy/core/src/multiarray/getset.c#L500-L555 # noqa: E501 

2713 def impl(a, dtype): 

2714 dtype_size = _intrin_get_itemsize(dtype) 

2715 if dtype_size != a.itemsize: 

2716 # catch forbidden cases 

2717 if a.ndim == 0: 

2718 msg1 = ("Changing the dtype of a 0d array is only supported " 

2719 "if the itemsize is unchanged") 

2720 raise ValueError(msg1) 

2721 else: 

2722 # NumPy has a check here for subarray type conversion which 

2723 # Numba doesn't support 

2724 pass 

2725 

2726 # Resize on last axis only 

2727 axis = a.ndim - 1 

2728 p1 = a.shape[axis] != 1 

2729 p2 = a.size != 0 

2730 p3 = a.strides[axis] != a.itemsize 

2731 if (p1 and p2 and p3): 

2732 msg2 = ("To change to a dtype of a different size, the last " 

2733 "axis must be contiguous") 

2734 raise ValueError(msg2) 

2735 

2736 if dtype_size < a.itemsize: 

2737 if dtype_size == 0 or a.itemsize % dtype_size != 0: 

2738 msg3 = ("When changing to a smaller dtype, its size must " 

2739 "be a divisor of the size of original dtype") 

2740 raise ValueError(msg3) 

2741 else: 

2742 newdim = a.shape[axis] * a.itemsize 

2743 if newdim % dtype_size != 0: 

2744 msg4 = ("When changing to a larger dtype, its size must be " 

2745 "a divisor of the total size in bytes of the last " 

2746 "axis of the array.") 

2747 raise ValueError(msg4) 

2748 return impl

2751@lower_builtin('array.view', types.Array, types.DTypeSpec) 

2752def array_view(context, builder, sig, args): 

2753 aryty = sig.args[0] 

2754 retty = sig.return_type 

2755 

2756 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, args[0]) 

2757 ret = make_array(retty)(context, builder) 

2758 # Copy all fields, casting the "data" pointer appropriately 

2759 fields = set(ret._datamodel._fields) 

2760 for k in sorted(fields): 

2761 val = getattr(ary, k) 

2762 if k == 'data': 

2763 ptrty = ret.data.type 

2764 ret.data = builder.bitcast(val, ptrty) 

2765 else: 

2766 setattr(ret, k, val) 

2767 

2768 tyctx = context.typing_context 

2769 fnty = tyctx.resolve_value_type(_compatible_view) 

2770 _compatible_view_sig = fnty.get_call_type(tyctx, (*sig.args,), {}) 

2771 impl = context.get_function(fnty, _compatible_view_sig) 

2772 impl(builder, args) 

2773 

2774 ok = _change_dtype(context, builder, aryty, retty, ret) 

2775 fail = builder.icmp_unsigned('==', ok, Constant(ok.type, 0)) 

2776 

2777 with builder.if_then(fail): 

2778 msg = "new type not compatible with array" 

2779 context.call_conv.return_user_exc(builder, ValueError, (msg,)) 

2780 

2781 res = ret._getvalue() 

2782 return impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, sig.return_type, res)

2905def _call_contiguous_check(checker, context, builder, aryty, ary): 

2906 """Helper to invoke the contiguous checker function on an array 

2907 

2908 Args 

2909 ---- 

2910 checker : 

2911 ``numba.numpy_supports.is_contiguous``, or 

2912 ``numba.numpy_supports.is_fortran``. 

2913 context : target context 

2914 builder : llvm ir builder 

2915 aryty : numba type 

2916 ary : llvm value 

2917 """ 

2918 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, value=ary) 

2919 tup_intp = types.UniTuple(types.intp, aryty.ndim) 

2920 itemsize = context.get_abi_sizeof(context.get_value_type(aryty.dtype)) 

2921 check_sig = signature(types.bool_, tup_intp, tup_intp, types.intp) 

2922 check_args = [ary.shape, ary.strides, 

2923 context.get_constant(types.intp, itemsize)] 

2924 is_contig = context.compile_internal(builder, checker, check_sig, 

2925 check_args) 

2926 return is_contig

2998 

2999def array_complex_attr(context, builder, typ, value, attr): 

3000 """ 

3001 Given a complex array, it's memory layout is: 

3002 

3003 R C R C R C 

3004 ^ ^ ^ 

3005 

3006 (`R` indicates a float for the real part; 

3007 `C` indicates a float for the imaginary part; 

3008 the `^` indicates the start of each element) 

3009 

3010 To get the real part, we can simply change the dtype and itemsize to that 

3011 of the underlying float type. The new layout is: 

3012 

3013 R x R x R x 

3014 ^ ^ ^ 

3015 

3016 (`x` indicates unused) 

3017 

3018 A load operation will use the dtype to determine the number of bytes to 

3019 load. 

3020 

3021 To get the imaginary part, we shift the pointer by 1 float offset and 

3022 change the dtype and itemsize. The new layout is: 

3023 

3024 x C x C x C 

3025 ^ ^ ^ 

3026 """ 

3027 if attr not in ['real', 'imag'] or typ.dtype not in types.complex_domain: 

3028 raise NotImplementedError("cannot get attribute `{}`".format(attr)) 

3029 

3030 arrayty = make_array(typ) 

3031 array = arrayty(context, builder, value) 

3032 

3033 # sizeof underlying float type 

3034 flty = typ.dtype.underlying_float 

3035 sizeof_flty = context.get_abi_sizeof(context.get_data_type(flty)) 

3036 itemsize = array.itemsize.type(sizeof_flty) 

3037 

3038 # cast data pointer to float type 

3039 llfltptrty = context.get_value_type(flty).as_pointer() 

3040 dataptr = builder.bitcast(array.data, llfltptrty) 

3041 

3042 # add offset 

3043 if attr == 'imag': 

3044 dataptr = builder.gep(dataptr, [ir.IntType(32)(1)]) 

3045 

3046 # make result 

3047 resultty = typ.copy(dtype=flty, layout='A') 

3048 result = make_array(resultty)(context, builder) 

3049 repl = dict(data=dataptr, itemsize=itemsize) 

3050 cgutils.copy_struct(result, array, repl) 

3051 return impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, resultty, result._getvalue())

3207@lower_setattr_generic(types.Record)

3210 Generic setattr() implementation for records: set the given record member. 

3211 """

3214

3216 offset = typ.offset(attr)

3234 context.pack_value(builder, elemty, val, dptr, align=align)

3360def _increment_indices(context, builder, ndim, shape, indices, end_flag=None, 

3361 loop_continue=None, loop_break=None): 

3362 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3363 

3364 bbend = builder.append_basic_block('end_increment') 

3365 

3366 if end_flag is not None: 

3367 builder.store(cgutils.false_byte, end_flag) 

3368 

3369 for dim in reversed(range(ndim)): 

3370 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3371 idx = cgutils.increment_index(builder, builder.load(idxptr)) 

3372 

3373 count = shape[dim] 

3374 in_bounds = builder.icmp_signed('<', idx, count) 

3375 with cgutils.if_likely(builder, in_bounds): 

3376 # New index is still in bounds 

3377 builder.store(idx, idxptr) 

3378 if loop_continue is not None: 

3379 loop_continue(dim) 

3380 builder.branch(bbend) 

3381 # Index out of bounds => reset it and proceed it to outer index 

3382 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3383 if loop_break is not None: 

3384 loop_break(dim) 

3385 

3386 if end_flag is not None: 

3387 builder.store(cgutils.true_byte, end_flag) 

3388 builder.branch(bbend) 

3389 

3390 builder.position_at_end(bbend) 

3391 

3392 

3393def _increment_indices_array(context, builder, arrty, arr, indices, 

3394 end_flag=None): 

3395 shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape, arrty.ndim) 

3396 _increment_indices(context, builder, arrty.ndim, shape, indices, end_flag)
