3409 class BaseSubIter(object): 

3410 """ 

3411 Base class for sub-iterators of a nditer() instance. 

3412 """ 

3413 

3414 def __init__(self, nditer, member_name, start_dim, end_dim): 

3415 self.nditer = nditer 

3416 self.member_name = member_name 

3417 self.start_dim = start_dim 

3418 self.end_dim = end_dim 

3419 self.ndim = end_dim - start_dim 

3420 

3421 def set_member_ptr(self, ptr): 

3422 setattr(self.nditer, self.member_name, ptr) 

3423 

3424 @functools.cached_property 

3425 def member_ptr(self): 

3426 return getattr(self.nditer, self.member_name) 

3427 

3428 def init_specific(self, context, builder): 

3429 pass 

3430 

3431 def loop_continue(self, context, builder, logical_dim): 

3432 pass 

3433 

3434 def loop_break(self, context, builder, logical_dim): 

3435 pass 

3436 

3437 class FlatSubIter(BaseSubIter): 

3438 """ 

3439 Sub-iterator walking a contiguous array in physical order, with 

3440 support for broadcasting (the index is reset on the outer dimension). 

3441 """ 

3442 

3443 def init_specific(self, context, builder): 

3444 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3445 self.set_member_ptr(cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, zero)) 

3446 

3447 def compute_pointer(self, context, builder, indices, arrty, arr): 

3448 index = builder.load(self.member_ptr) 

3449 return builder.gep(arr.data, [index]) 

3450 

3451 def loop_continue(self, context, builder, logical_dim): 

3452 if logical_dim == self.ndim - 1: 

3453 # Only increment index inside innermost logical dimension 

3454 index = builder.load(self.member_ptr) 

3455 index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, index) 

3456 builder.store(index, self.member_ptr) 

3457 

3458 def loop_break(self, context, builder, logical_dim): 

3459 if logical_dim == 0: 

3460 # At the exit of outermost logical dimension, reset index 

3461 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3462 builder.store(zero, self.member_ptr) 

3463 elif logical_dim == self.ndim - 1: 

3464 # Inside innermost logical dimension, increment index 

3465 index = builder.load(self.member_ptr) 

3466 index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, index) 

3467 builder.store(index, self.member_ptr) 

3468 

3469 class TrivialFlatSubIter(BaseSubIter): 

3470 """ 

3471 Sub-iterator walking a contiguous array in physical order, 

3472 *without* support for broadcasting. 

3473 """ 

3474 

3475 def init_specific(self, context, builder): 

3476 assert not nditerty.need_shaped_indexing 

3477 

3478 def compute_pointer(self, context, builder, indices, arrty, arr): 

3479 assert len(indices) <= 1, len(indices) 

3480 return builder.gep(arr.data, indices) 

3481 

3482 class IndexedSubIter(BaseSubIter): 

3483 """ 

3484 Sub-iterator walking an array in logical order. 

3485 """ 

3486 

3487 def compute_pointer(self, context, builder, indices, arrty, arr): 

3488 assert len(indices) == self.ndim 

3489 return cgutils.get_item_pointer(context, builder, arrty, arr, 

3490 indices, wraparound=False) 

3491 

3492 class ZeroDimSubIter(BaseSubIter): 

3493 """ 

3494 Sub-iterator "walking" a 0-d array. 

3495 """ 

3496 

3497 def compute_pointer(self, context, builder, indices, arrty, arr): 

3498 return arr.data 

3499 

3500 class ScalarSubIter(BaseSubIter): 

3501 """ 

3502 Sub-iterator "walking" a scalar value. 

3503 """ 

3504 

3505 def compute_pointer(self, context, builder, indices, arrty, arr): 

3506 return arr 

3507 

3508 class NdIter(cgutils.create_struct_proxy(nditerty)): 

3509 """ 

3510 .nditer() implementation. 

3511 

3512 Note: 'F' layout means the shape is iterated in reverse logical order, 

3513 so indices and shapes arrays have to be reversed as well. 

3514 """ 

3515 

3516 @functools.cached_property 

3517 def subiters(self): 

3518 l = [] 

3519 factories = {'flat': FlatSubIter if nditerty.need_shaped_indexing 

3520 else TrivialFlatSubIter, 

3521 'indexed': IndexedSubIter, 

3522 '0d': ZeroDimSubIter, 

3523 'scalar': ScalarSubIter, 

3524 } 

3525 for i, sub in enumerate(nditerty.indexers): 

3526 kind, start_dim, end_dim, _ = sub 

3527 member_name = 'index%d' % i 

3528 factory = factories[kind] 

3529 l.append(factory(self, member_name, start_dim, end_dim)) 

3530 return l 

3531 

3532 def init_specific(self, context, builder, arrtys, arrays): 

3533 """ 

3534 Initialize the nditer() instance for the specific array inputs. 

3535 """ 

3536 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3537 

3538 # Store inputs 

3539 self.arrays = context.make_tuple(builder, types.Tuple(arrtys), 

3540 arrays) 

3541 # Create slots for scalars 

3542 for i, ty in enumerate(arrtys): 

3543 if not isinstance(ty, types.Array): 

3544 member_name = 'scalar%d' % i 

3545 # XXX as_data()? 

3546 slot = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, arrays[i]) 

3547 setattr(self, member_name, slot) 

3548 

3549 arrays = self._arrays_or_scalars(context, builder, arrtys, arrays) 

3550 

3551 # Extract iterator shape (the shape of the most-dimensional input) 

3552 main_shape_ty = types.UniTuple(types.intp, ndim) 

3553 main_shape = None 

3554 main_nitems = None 

3555 for i, arrty in enumerate(arrtys): 

3556 if isinstance(arrty, types.Array) and arrty.ndim == ndim: 

3557 main_shape = arrays[i].shape 

3558 main_nitems = arrays[i].nitems 

3559 break 

3560 else: 

3561 # Only scalar inputs => synthesize a dummy shape 

3562 assert ndim == 0 

3563 main_shape = context.make_tuple(builder, main_shape_ty, ()) 

3564 main_nitems = context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

3565 

3566 # Validate shapes of array inputs 

3567 def check_shape(shape, main_shape): 

3568 n = len(shape) 

3569 for i in range(n): 

3570 if shape[i] != main_shape[len(main_shape) - n + i]: 

3571 raise ValueError("nditer(): operands could not be " 

3572 "broadcast together") 

3573 

3574 for arrty, arr in zip(arrtys, arrays): 

3575 if isinstance(arrty, types.Array) and arrty.ndim > 0: 

3576 sig = signature(types.none, 

3577 types.UniTuple(types.intp, arrty.ndim), 

3578 main_shape_ty) 

3579 context.compile_internal(builder, check_shape, 

3580 sig, (arr.shape, main_shape)) 

3581 

3582 # Compute shape and size 

3583 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, main_shape) 

3584 if layout == 'F': 

3585 shapes = shapes[::-1] 

3586 

3587 # If shape is empty, mark iterator exhausted 

3588 shape_is_empty = builder.icmp_signed('==', main_nitems, zero) 

3589 exhausted = builder.select(shape_is_empty, cgutils.true_byte, 

3590 cgutils.false_byte) 

3591 

3592 if not nditerty.need_shaped_indexing: 

3593 # Flatten shape to make iteration faster on small innermost 

3594 # dimensions (e.g. a (100000, 3) shape) 

3595 shapes = (main_nitems,) 

3596 assert len(shapes) == nshapes 

3597 

3598 indices = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, zero.type, size=nshapes) 

3599 for dim in range(nshapes): 

3600 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3601 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3602 

3603 self.indices = indices 

3604 self.shape = cgutils.pack_array(builder, shapes, zero.type) 

3605 self.exhausted = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, exhausted) 

3606 

3607 # Initialize subiterators 

3608 for subiter in self.subiters: 

3609 subiter.init_specific(context, builder) 

3610 

3611 def iternext_specific(self, context, builder, result): 

3612 """ 

3613 Compute next iteration of the nditer() instance. 

3614 """ 

3615 bbend = builder.append_basic_block('end') 

3616 

3617 # Branch early if exhausted 

3618 exhausted = cgutils.as_bool_bit(builder, 

3619 builder.load(self.exhausted)) 

3620 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, exhausted): 

3621 result.set_valid(False) 

3622 builder.branch(bbend) 

3623 

3624 arrtys = nditerty.arrays 

3625 arrays = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, self.arrays) 

3626 arrays = self._arrays_or_scalars(context, builder, arrtys, arrays) 

3627 indices = self.indices 

3628 

3629 # Compute iterated results 

3630 result.set_valid(True) 

3631 views = self._make_views(context, builder, indices, arrtys, arrays) 

3632 views = [v._getvalue() for v in views] 

3633 if len(views) == 1: 

3634 result.yield_(views[0]) 

3635 else: 

3636 result.yield_(context.make_tuple(builder, nditerty.yield_type, 

3637 views)) 

3638 

3639 shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, self.shape) 

3640 _increment_indices(context, builder, len(shape), shape, 

3641 indices, self.exhausted, 

3642 functools.partial(self._loop_continue, 

3643 context, 

3644 builder), 

3645 functools.partial(self._loop_break, 

3646 context, 

3647 builder), 

3648 ) 

3649 

3650 builder.branch(bbend) 

3651 builder.position_at_end(bbend) 

3652 

3653 def _loop_continue(self, context, builder, dim): 

3654 for sub in self.subiters: 

3655 if sub.start_dim <= dim < sub.end_dim: 

3656 sub.loop_continue(context, builder, dim - sub.start_dim) 

3657 

3658 def _loop_break(self, context, builder, dim): 

3659 for sub in self.subiters: 

3660 if sub.start_dim <= dim < sub.end_dim: 

3661 sub.loop_break(context, builder, dim - sub.start_dim) 

3662 

3663 def _make_views(self, context, builder, indices, arrtys, arrays): 

3664 """ 

3665 Compute the views to be yielded. 

3666 """ 

3667 views = [None] * narrays 

3668 indexers = nditerty.indexers 

3669 subiters = self.subiters 

3670 rettys = nditerty.yield_type 

3671 if isinstance(rettys, types.BaseTuple): 

3672 rettys = list(rettys) 

3673 else: 

3674 rettys = [rettys] 

3675 indices = [builder.load(cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, i)) 

3676 for i in range(nshapes)] 

3677 

3678 for sub, subiter in zip(indexers, subiters): 

3679 _, _, _, array_indices = sub 

3680 sub_indices = indices[subiter.start_dim:subiter.end_dim] 

3681 if layout == 'F': 

3682 sub_indices = sub_indices[::-1] 

3683 for i in array_indices: 

3684 assert views[i] is None 

3685 views[i] = self._make_view(context, builder, sub_indices, 

3686 rettys[i], 

3687 arrtys[i], arrays[i], subiter) 

3688 assert all(v for v in views) 

3689 return views 

3690 

3691 def _make_view(self, context, builder, indices, retty, arrty, arr, 

3692 subiter): 

3693 """ 

3694 Compute a 0d view for a given input array. 

3695 """ 

3696 assert isinstance(retty, types.Array) and retty.ndim == 0 

3697 

3698 ptr = subiter.compute_pointer(context, builder, indices, arrty, arr) 

3699 view = context.make_array(retty)(context, builder) 

3700 

3701 itemsize = get_itemsize(context, retty) 

3702 shape = context.make_tuple(builder, types.UniTuple(types.intp, 0), 

3703 ()) 

3704 strides = context.make_tuple(builder, types.UniTuple(types.intp, 0), 

3705 ()) 

3706 # HACK: meminfo=None avoids expensive refcounting operations 

3707 # on ephemeral views 

3708 populate_array(view, ptr, shape, strides, itemsize, meminfo=None) 

3709 return view 

3710 

3711 def _arrays_or_scalars(self, context, builder, arrtys, arrays): 

3712 # Return a list of either array structures or pointers to 

3713 # scalar slots 

3714 l = [] 

3715 for i, (arrty, arr) in enumerate(zip(arrtys, arrays)): 

3716 if isinstance(arrty, types.Array): 

3717 l.append(context.make_array(arrty)(context, 

3718 builder, 

3719 value=arr)) 

3720 else: 

3721 l.append(getattr(self, "scalar%d" % i)) 

3722 return l 

3723 

3724 return NdIter

3727def make_ndindex_cls(nditerty): 

3728 """ 

3729 Return the Structure representation of the given *nditerty* (an 

3730 instance of types.NumpyNdIndexType). 

3731 """ 

3732 ndim = nditerty.ndim 

3733 

3734 class NdIndexIter(cgutils.create_struct_proxy(nditerty)): 

3735 """ 

3736 .ndindex() implementation. 

3737 """ 

3738 

3739 def init_specific(self, context, builder, shapes): 

3740 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3741 indices = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, zero.type, 

3742 size=context.get_constant(types.intp, 

3743 ndim)) 

3744 exhausted = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, cgutils.false_byte) 

3745 

3746 for dim in range(ndim): 

3747 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3748 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3749 # 0-sized dimensions really indicate an empty array, 

3750 # but we have to catch that condition early to avoid 

3751 # a bug inside the iteration logic. 

3752 dim_size = shapes[dim] 

3753 dim_is_empty = builder.icmp_unsigned('==', dim_size, zero) 

3754 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, dim_is_empty): 

3755 builder.store(cgutils.true_byte, exhausted) 

3756 

3757 self.indices = indices 

3758 self.exhausted = exhausted 

3759 self.shape = cgutils.pack_array(builder, shapes, zero.type) 

3760 

3761 def iternext_specific(self, context, builder, result): 

3762 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3763 

3764 bbend = builder.append_basic_block('end') 

3765 

3766 exhausted = cgutils.as_bool_bit(builder, 

3767 builder.load(self.exhausted)) 

3768 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, exhausted): 

3769 result.set_valid(False) 

3770 builder.branch(bbend) 

3771 

3772 indices = [builder.load(cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

3773 self.indices, 

3774 dim)) 

3775 for dim in range(ndim)] 

3776 for load in indices: 

3777 mark_positive(builder, load) 

3778 

3779 result.yield_(cgutils.pack_array(builder, indices, zero.type)) 

3780 result.set_valid(True) 

3781 

3782 shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, self.shape, ndim) 

3783 _increment_indices(context, builder, ndim, shape, 

3784 self.indices, self.exhausted) 

3785 

3786 builder.branch(bbend) 

3787 builder.position_at_end(bbend) 

3788 

3789 return NdIndexIter

3792def _make_flattening_iter_cls(flatiterty, kind): 

3793 assert kind in ('flat', 'ndenumerate') 

3794 

3795 array_type = flatiterty.array_type 

3796 

3797 if array_type.layout == 'C': 

3798 class CContiguousFlatIter(cgutils.create_struct_proxy(flatiterty)): 

3799 """ 

3800 .flat() / .ndenumerate() implementation for C-contiguous arrays. 

3801 """ 

3802 

3803 def init_specific(self, context, builder, arrty, arr): 

3804 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3805 self.index = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, zero) 

3806 # We can't trust strides[-1] to always contain the right 

3807 # step value, see 

3808 # http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy-dev/release.html#npy-relaxed-strides-checking # noqa: E501 

3809 self.stride = arr.itemsize 

3810 

3811 if kind == 'ndenumerate': 

3812 # Zero-initialize the indices array. 

3813 indices = cgutils.alloca_once( 

3814 builder, zero.type, 

3815 size=context.get_constant(types.intp, arrty.ndim)) 

3816 

3817 for dim in range(arrty.ndim): 

3818 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3819 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3820 

3821 self.indices = indices 

3822 

3823 # NOTE: Using gep() instead of explicit pointer addition helps 

3824 # LLVM vectorize the loop (since the stride is known and 

3825 # constant). This is not possible in the non-contiguous case, 

3826 # where the strides are unknown at compile-time. 

3827 

3828 def iternext_specific(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, result): 

3829 ndim = arrty.ndim 

3830 nitems = arr.nitems 

3831 

3832 index = builder.load(self.index) 

3833 is_valid = builder.icmp_signed('<', index, nitems) 

3834 result.set_valid(is_valid) 

3835 

3836 with cgutils.if_likely(builder, is_valid): 

3837 ptr = builder.gep(arr.data, [index]) 

3838 value = load_item(context, builder, arrty, ptr) 

3839 if kind == 'flat': 

3840 result.yield_(value) 

3841 else: 

3842 # ndenumerate(): fetch and increment indices 

3843 indices = self.indices 

3844 idxvals = [builder.load(cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

3845 indices, 

3846 dim)) 

3847 for dim in range(ndim)] 

3848 idxtuple = cgutils.pack_array(builder, idxvals) 

3849 result.yield_( 

3850 cgutils.make_anonymous_struct(builder, 

3851 [idxtuple, value])) 

3852 _increment_indices_array(context, builder, arrty, 

3853 arr, indices) 

3854 

3855 index = cgutils.increment_index(builder, index) 

3856 builder.store(index, self.index) 

3857 

3858 def getitem(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, index): 

3859 ptr = builder.gep(arr.data, [index]) 

3860 return load_item(context, builder, arrty, ptr) 

3861 

3862 def setitem(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, index, value): 

3863 ptr = builder.gep(arr.data, [index]) 

3864 store_item(context, builder, arrty, value, ptr) 

3865 

3866 return CContiguousFlatIter 

3867 

3868 else: 

3869 class FlatIter(cgutils.create_struct_proxy(flatiterty)): 

3870 """ 

3871 Generic .flat() / .ndenumerate() implementation for 

3872 non-contiguous arrays. 

3873 It keeps track of pointers along each dimension in order to 

3874 minimize computations. 

3875 """ 

3876 

3877 def init_specific(self, context, builder, arrty, arr): 

3878 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3879 data = arr.data 

3880 ndim = arrty.ndim 

3881 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape, ndim) 

3882 

3883 indices = cgutils.alloca_once( 

3884 builder, zero.type, size=context.get_constant(types.intp, 

3885 arrty.ndim)) 

3886 pointers = cgutils.alloca_once( 

3887 builder, data.type, size=context.get_constant(types.intp, 

3888 arrty.ndim)) 

3889 exhausted = cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, 

3890 cgutils.false_byte) 

3891 

3892 # Initialize indices and pointers with their start values. 

3893 for dim in range(ndim): 

3894 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3895 ptrptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, pointers, dim) 

3896 builder.store(data, ptrptr) 

3897 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3898 # 0-sized dimensions really indicate an empty array, 

3899 # but we have to catch that condition early to avoid 

3900 # a bug inside the iteration logic (see issue #846). 

3901 dim_size = shapes[dim] 

3902 dim_is_empty = builder.icmp_unsigned('==', dim_size, zero) 

3903 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, dim_is_empty): 

3904 builder.store(cgutils.true_byte, exhausted) 

3905 

3906 self.indices = indices 

3907 self.pointers = pointers 

3908 self.exhausted = exhausted 

3909 

3910 def iternext_specific(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, result): 

3911 ndim = arrty.ndim 

3912 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape, ndim) 

3913 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.strides, ndim) 

3914 indices = self.indices 

3915 pointers = self.pointers 

3916 

3917 zero = context.get_constant(types.intp, 0) 

3918 

3919 bbend = builder.append_basic_block('end') 

3920 

3921 # Catch already computed iterator exhaustion 

3922 is_exhausted = cgutils.as_bool_bit( 

3923 builder, builder.load(self.exhausted)) 

3924 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, is_exhausted): 

3925 result.set_valid(False) 

3926 builder.branch(bbend) 

3927 result.set_valid(True) 

3928 

3929 # Current pointer inside last dimension 

3930 last_ptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, pointers, ndim - 1) 

3931 ptr = builder.load(last_ptr) 

3932 value = load_item(context, builder, arrty, ptr) 

3933 if kind == 'flat': 

3934 result.yield_(value) 

3935 else: 

3936 # ndenumerate() => yield (indices, value) 

3937 idxvals = [builder.load(cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

3938 indices, 

3939 dim)) 

3940 for dim in range(ndim)] 

3941 idxtuple = cgutils.pack_array(builder, idxvals) 

3942 result.yield_( 

3943 cgutils.make_anonymous_struct(builder, 

3944 [idxtuple, value])) 

3945 

3946 # Update indices and pointers by walking from inner 

3947 # dimension to outer. 

3948 for dim in reversed(range(ndim)): 

3949 idxptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, indices, dim) 

3950 idx = cgutils.increment_index(builder, 

3951 builder.load(idxptr)) 

3952 

3953 count = shapes[dim] 

3954 stride = strides[dim] 

3955 in_bounds = builder.icmp_signed('<', idx, count) 

3956 with cgutils.if_likely(builder, in_bounds): 

3957 # Index is valid => pointer can simply be incremented. 

3958 builder.store(idx, idxptr) 

3959 ptrptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, pointers, dim) 

3960 ptr = builder.load(ptrptr) 

3961 ptr = cgutils.pointer_add(builder, ptr, stride) 

3962 builder.store(ptr, ptrptr) 

3963 # Reset pointers in inner dimensions 

3964 for inner_dim in range(dim + 1, ndim): 

3965 ptrptr = cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

3966 pointers, 

3967 inner_dim) 

3968 builder.store(ptr, ptrptr) 

3969 builder.branch(bbend) 

3970 # Reset index and continue with next dimension 

3971 builder.store(zero, idxptr) 

3972 

3973 # End of array 

3974 builder.store(cgutils.true_byte, self.exhausted) 

3975 builder.branch(bbend) 

3976 

3977 builder.position_at_end(bbend) 

3978 

3979 def _ptr_for_index(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, index): 

3980 ndim = arrty.ndim 

3981 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape, count=ndim) 

3982 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.strides, count=ndim) 

3983 

3984 # First convert the flattened index into a regular n-dim index 

3985 indices = [] 

3986 for dim in reversed(range(ndim)): 

3987 indices.append(builder.urem(index, shapes[dim])) 

3988 index = builder.udiv(index, shapes[dim]) 

3989 indices.reverse() 

3990 

3991 ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, arr.data, 

3992 shapes, strides, arrty.layout, 

3993 indices) 

3994 return ptr 

3995 

3996 def getitem(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, index): 

3997 ptr = self._ptr_for_index(context, builder, arrty, arr, index) 

3998 return load_item(context, builder, arrty, ptr) 

3999 

4000 def setitem(self, context, builder, arrty, arr, index, value): 

4001 ptr = self._ptr_for_index(context, builder, arrty, arr, index) 

4002 store_item(context, builder, arrty, value, ptr) 

4003 

4004 return FlatIter

4207def _empty_nd_impl(context, builder, arrtype, shapes): 

4208 """Utility function used for allocating a new array during LLVM code 

4209 generation (lowering). Given a target context, builder, array 

4210 type, and a tuple or list of lowered dimension sizes, returns a 

4211 LLVM value pointing at a Numba runtime allocated array. 

4212 """ 

4213 arycls = make_array(arrtype) 

4214 ary = arycls(context, builder) 

4215 

4216 datatype = context.get_data_type(arrtype.dtype) 

4217 itemsize = context.get_constant(types.intp, get_itemsize(context, arrtype)) 

4218 

4219 # compute array length 

4220 arrlen = context.get_constant(types.intp, 1) 

4221 overflow = Constant(ir.IntType(1), 0) 

4222 for s in shapes: 

4223 arrlen_mult = builder.smul_with_overflow(arrlen, s) 

4224 arrlen = builder.extract_value(arrlen_mult, 0) 

4225 overflow = builder.or_( 

4226 overflow, builder.extract_value(arrlen_mult, 1) 

4227 ) 

4228 

4229 if arrtype.ndim == 0: 

4230 strides = () 

4231 elif arrtype.layout == 'C': 

4232 strides = [itemsize] 

4233 for dimension_size in reversed(shapes[1:]): 

4234 strides.append(builder.mul(strides[-1], dimension_size)) 

4235 strides = tuple(reversed(strides)) 

4236 elif arrtype.layout == 'F': 

4237 strides = [itemsize] 

4238 for dimension_size in shapes[:-1]: 

4239 strides.append(builder.mul(strides[-1], dimension_size)) 

4240 strides = tuple(strides) 

4241 else: 

4242 raise NotImplementedError( 

4243 "Don't know how to allocate array with layout '{0}'.".format( 

4244 arrtype.layout)) 

4245 

4246 # Check overflow, numpy also does this after checking order 

4247 allocsize_mult = builder.smul_with_overflow(arrlen, itemsize) 

4248 allocsize = builder.extract_value(allocsize_mult, 0) 

4249 overflow = builder.or_(overflow, builder.extract_value(allocsize_mult, 1)) 

4250 

4251 with builder.if_then(overflow, likely=False): 

4252 # Raise same error as numpy, see: 

4253 # https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/2a488fe76a0f732dc418d03b452caace161673da/numpy/core/src/multiarray/ctors.c#L1095-L1101 # noqa: E501 

4254 context.call_conv.return_user_exc( 

4255 builder, ValueError, 

4256 ("array is too big; `arr.size * arr.dtype.itemsize` is larger than" 

4257 " the maximum possible size.",) 

4258 ) 

4259 

4260 dtype = arrtype.dtype 

4261 align_val = context.get_preferred_array_alignment(dtype) 

4262 align = context.get_constant(types.uint32, align_val) 

4263 args = (context.get_dummy_value(), allocsize, align) 

4264 

4265 mip = types.MemInfoPointer(types.voidptr) 

4266 arytypeclass = types.TypeRef(type(arrtype)) 

4267 argtypes = signature(mip, arytypeclass, types.intp, types.uint32) 

4268 

4269 meminfo = context.compile_internal(builder, _call_allocator, argtypes, args) 

4270 data = context.nrt.meminfo_data(builder, meminfo) 

4271 

4272 intp_t = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

4273 shape_array = cgutils.pack_array(builder, shapes, ty=intp_t) 

4274 strides_array = cgutils.pack_array(builder, strides, ty=intp_t) 

4275 

4276 populate_array(ary, 

4277 data=builder.bitcast(data, datatype.as_pointer()), 

4278 shape=shape_array, 

4279 strides=strides_array, 

4280 itemsize=itemsize, 

4281 meminfo=meminfo) 

4282 

4283 return ary

4316def _parse_shape(context, builder, ty, val): 

4317 """ 

4318 Parse the shape argument to an array constructor. 

4319 """ 

4320 def safecast_intp(context, builder, src_t, src): 

4321 """Cast src to intp only if value can be maintained""" 

4322 intp_t = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

4323 intp_width = intp_t.width 

4324 intp_ir = ir.IntType(intp_width) 

4325 maxval = Constant(intp_ir, ((1 << intp_width - 1) - 1)) 

4326 if src_t.width < intp_width: 

4327 res = builder.sext(src, intp_ir) 

4328 elif src_t.width >= intp_width: 

4329 is_larger = builder.icmp_signed(">", src, maxval) 

4330 with builder.if_then(is_larger, likely=False): 

4331 context.call_conv.return_user_exc( 

4332 builder, ValueError, 

4333 ("Cannot safely convert value to intp",) 

4334 ) 

4335 if src_t.width > intp_width: 

4336 res = builder.trunc(src, intp_ir) 

4337 else: 

4338 res = src 

4339 return res 

4340 

4341 if isinstance(ty, types.Integer): 

4342 ndim = 1 

4343 passed_shapes = [context.cast(builder, val, ty, types.intp)] 

4344 else: 

4345 assert isinstance(ty, types.BaseTuple) 

4346 ndim = ty.count 

4347 passed_shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, val, count=ndim) 

4348 

4349 shapes = [] 

4350 for s in passed_shapes: 

4351 shapes.append(safecast_intp(context, builder, s.type, s)) 

4352 

4353 zero = context.get_constant_generic(builder, types.intp, 0) 

4354 for dim in range(ndim): 

4355 is_neg = builder.icmp_signed('<', shapes[dim], zero) 

4356 with cgutils.if_unlikely(builder, is_neg): 

4357 context.call_conv.return_user_exc( 

4358 builder, ValueError, ("negative dimensions not allowed",) 

4359 ) 

4360 

4361 return shapes

4598@extending.overload(np.eye) 

4599def numpy_eye(N, M=None, k=0, dtype=float): 

4600 

4601 if dtype is None or isinstance(dtype, types.NoneType): 

4602 dt = np.dtype(float) 

4603 elif isinstance(dtype, (types.DTypeSpec, types.Number)): 

4604 # dtype or instance of dtype 

4605 dt = as_dtype(getattr(dtype, 'dtype', dtype)) 

4606 else:

4610 _M = _eye_none_handler(N, M)

4612 if k >= 0: 

4613 d = min(N, _M - k) 

4614 for i in range(d): 

4615 arr[i, i + k] = 1 

4616 else:

4618 for i in range(d): 

4619 arr[i - k, i] = 1

4624@overload(np.diag) 

4625def impl_np_diag(v, k=0): 

4626 if not type_can_asarray(v): 

4627 raise errors.TypingError('The argument "v" must be array-like') 

4628 

4629 if isinstance(v, types.Array): 

4630 if v.ndim not in (1, 2): 

4631 raise errors.NumbaTypeError("Input must be 1- or 2-d.") 

4632 

4633 def diag_impl(v, k=0): 

4634 if v.ndim == 1: 

4635 s = v.shape 

4636 n = s[0] + abs(k) 

4637 ret = np.zeros((n, n), v.dtype) 

4638 if k >= 0: 

4639 for i in range(n - k): 

4640 ret[i, k + i] = v[i] 

4641 else: 

4642 for i in range(n + k): 

4643 ret[i - k, i] = v[i] 

4644 return ret 

4645 else: # 2-d 

4646 rows, cols = v.shape 

4647 if k < 0: 

4648 rows = rows + k 

4649 if k > 0: 

4650 cols = cols - k 

4651 n = max(min(rows, cols), 0) 

4652 ret = np.empty(n, v.dtype) 

4653 if k >= 0: 

4654 for i in range(n): 

4655 ret[i] = v[i, k + i] 

4656 else: 

4657 for i in range(n): 

4658 ret[i] = v[i - k, i] 

4659 return ret 

4660 return diag_impl

4691@overload(np.diagflat) 

4692def numpy_diagflat(v, k=0): 

4693 if not type_can_asarray(v): 

4694 msg = 'The argument "v" must be array-like' 

4695 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

4696 

4697 if not isinstance(k, (int, types.Integer)): 

4698 msg = 'The argument "k" must be an integer' 

4699 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

4700 

4701 def impl(v, k=0): 

4702 v = np.asarray(v) 

4703 v = v.ravel() 

4704 s = len(v) 

4705 abs_k = abs(k) 

4706 n = s + abs_k 

4707 res = np.zeros((n, n), v.dtype) 

4708 i = np.maximum(0, -k) 

4709 j = np.maximum(0, k) 

4710 for t in range(s): 

4711 res[i + t, j + t] = v[t] 

4712 

4713 return res 

4714 

4715 return impl

4718def generate_getitem_setitem_with_axis(ndim, kind): 

4719 assert kind in ('getitem', 'setitem') 

4720 

4721 if kind == 'getitem': 

4722 fn = ''' 

4723 def _getitem(a, idx, axis): 

4724 if axis == 0: 

4725 return a[idx, ...] 

4726 ''' 

4727 for i in range(1, ndim): 

4728 lst = (':',) * i 

4729 fn += f''' 

4730 elif axis == {i}: 

4731 return a[{", ".join(lst)}, idx, ...] 

4732 ''' 

4733 else: 

4734 fn = ''' 

4735 def _setitem(a, idx, axis, vals): 

4736 if axis == 0: 

4737 a[idx, ...] = vals 

4738 ''' 

4739 

4740 for i in range(1, ndim): 

4741 lst = (':',) * i 

4742 fn += f''' 

4743 elif axis == {i}: 

4744 a[{", ".join(lst)}, idx, ...] = vals 

4745 ''' 

4746 

4747 fn = textwrap.dedent(fn) 

4748 exec(fn, globals()) 

4749 fn = globals()[f'_{kind}'] 

4750 return register_jitable(fn)

4845def _arange_dtype(*args): 

4846 bounds = [a for a in args if not isinstance(a, types.NoneType)] 

4847 

4848 if any(isinstance(a, types.Complex) for a in bounds): 

4849 dtype = types.complex128 

4850 elif any(isinstance(a, types.Float) for a in bounds): 

4851 dtype = types.float64 

4852 else: 

4853 # `np.arange(10).dtype` is always `np.dtype(int)`, aka `np.int_`, which 

4854 # in all released versions of numpy corresponds to the C `long` type. 

4855 # Windows 64 is broken by default here because Numba (as of 0.47) does 

4856 # not differentiate between Python and NumPy integers, so a `typeof(1)` 

4857 # on w64 is `int64`, i.e. `intp`. This means an arange(<some int>) will 

4858 # be typed as arange(int64) and the following will yield int64 opposed 

4859 # to int32. Example: without a load of analysis to work out of the args 

4860 # were wrapped in NumPy int*() calls it's not possible to detect the 

4861 # difference between `np.arange(10)` and `np.arange(np.int64(10)`. 

4862 NPY_TY = getattr(types, "int%s" % (8 * np.dtype(int).itemsize)) 

4863 

4864 # unliteral these types such that `max` works. 

4865 unliteral_bounds = [types.unliteral(x) for x in bounds] 

4866 dtype = max(unliteral_bounds + [NPY_TY,]) 

4867 

4868 return dtype

4871@overload(np.arange) 

4872def np_arange(start, / ,stop=None, step=None, dtype=None): 

4873 if isinstance(stop, types.Optional): 

4874 stop = stop.type 

4875 if isinstance(step, types.Optional): 

4876 step = step.type 

4877 if isinstance(dtype, types.Optional): 

4878 dtype = dtype.type 

4879 

4880 if stop is None: 

4881 stop = types.none 

4882 if step is None: 

4883 step = types.none 

4884 if dtype is None: 

4885 dtype = types.none 

4886 

4887 if (not isinstance(start, types.Number) or 

4888 not isinstance(stop, (types.NoneType, types.Number)) or 

4889 not isinstance(step, (types.NoneType, types.Number)) or 

4890 not isinstance(dtype, (types.NoneType, types.DTypeSpec))): 

4891 

4892 return 

4893 

4894 if isinstance(dtype, types.NoneType): 

4895 true_dtype = _arange_dtype(start, stop, step) 

4896 else: 

4897 true_dtype = dtype.dtype 

4898 

4899 use_complex = any([isinstance(x, types.Complex) 

4900 for x in (start, stop, step)]) 

4901 

4902 start_value = getattr(start, "literal_value", None) 

4903 stop_value = getattr(stop, "literal_value", None) 

4904 step_value = getattr(step, "literal_value", None) 

4905 

4906 def impl(start, /, stop=None, step=None, dtype=None): 

4907 # Allow for improved performance if given literal arguments. 

4908 lit_start = start_value if start_value is not None else start 

4909 lit_stop = stop_value if stop_value is not None else stop 

4910 lit_step = step_value if step_value is not None else step 

4911 

4912 _step = lit_step if lit_step is not None else 1 

4913 if lit_stop is None: 

4914 _start, _stop = 0, lit_start 

4915 else: 

4916 _start, _stop = lit_start, lit_stop 

4917 

4918 if _step == 0: 

4919 raise ValueError("Maximum allowed size exceeded") 

4920 

4921 nitems_c = (_stop - _start) / _step 

4922 nitems_r = int(math.ceil(nitems_c.real)) 

4923 

4924 # Binary operator needed for compiler branch pruning. 

4925 if use_complex is True: 

4926 nitems_i = int(math.ceil(nitems_c.imag)) 

4927 nitems = max(min(nitems_i, nitems_r), 0) 

4928 else: 

4929 nitems = max(nitems_r, 0) 

4930 arr = np.empty(nitems, true_dtype) 

4931 val = _start 

4932 for i in range(nitems): 

4933 arr[i] = val + (i * _step) 

4934 return arr 

4935 

4936 return impl

4939@overload(np.linspace) 

4940def numpy_linspace(start, stop, num=50): 

4941 if not all(isinstance(arg, types.Number) for arg in [start, stop]): 

4942 return 

4943 

4944 if not isinstance(num, (int, types.Integer)): 

4945 msg = 'The argument "num" must be an integer' 

4946 raise errors.TypingError(msg) 

4947 

4948 if any(isinstance(arg, types.Complex) for arg in [start, stop]): 

4949 if config.USE_LEGACY_TYPE_SYSTEM: 

4950 dtype = types.complex128 

4951 else: 

4952 dtype = types.np_complex128 

4953 else: 

4954 dtype = types.float64 

4955 

4956 # Implementation based on https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/v1.20.0/numpy/core/function_base.py#L24 # noqa: E501 

4957 def linspace(start, stop, num=50): 

4958 arr = np.empty(num, dtype) 

4959 # The multiply by 1.0 mirrors 

4960 # https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/v1.20.0/numpy/core/function_base.py#L125-L128 # noqa: E501 

4961 # the side effect of this is important... start and stop become the same 

4962 # type as `dtype` i.e. 64/128 bits wide (float/complex). This is 

4963 # important later when used in the `np.divide`. 

4964 start = start * 1.0 

4965 stop = stop * 1.0 

4966 if num == 0: 

4967 return arr 

4968 div = num - 1 

4969 if div > 0: 

4970 delta = stop - start 

4971 step = np.divide(delta, div) 

4972 for i in range(0, num): 

4973 arr[i] = start + (i * step) 

4974 else: 

4975 arr[0] = start 

4976 if num > 1: 

4977 arr[-1] = stop 

4978 return arr 

4979 return linspace

4984 Array copy. 

4985 """

4991 ret = _empty_nd_impl(context, builder, rettype, shapes) 

4992 

4993 src_data = ary.data 

4994 dest_data = ret.data 

4995 

4996 assert rettype.layout in "CF" 

4997 if arytype.layout == rettype.layout: 

4998 # Fast path: memcpy 

4999 cgutils.raw_memcpy(builder, dest_data, src_data, ary.nitems, 

5000 ary.itemsize, align=1) 

5001 

5002 else: 

5003 src_strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ary.strides) 

5004 dest_strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ret.strides)

5012 shapes, dest_strides, 

5013 rettype.layout, indices) 

5014 builder.store(builder.load(src_ptr), dest_ptr) 

5015

5041def _as_layout_array(context, builder, sig, args, output_layout): 

5042 """ 

5043 Common logic for layout conversion function; 

5044 e.g. ascontiguousarray and asfortranarray 

5045 """ 

5046 retty = sig.return_type 

5047 aryty = sig.args[0] 

5048 assert retty.layout == output_layout, 'return-type has incorrect layout' 

5049 

5050 if aryty.ndim == 0: 

5051 # 0-dim input => asfortranarray() returns a 1-dim array 

5052 assert retty.ndim == 1 

5053 ary = make_array(aryty)(context, builder, value=args[0]) 

5054 ret = make_array(retty)(context, builder) 

5055 

5056 shape = context.get_constant_generic( 

5057 builder, types.UniTuple(types.intp, 1), (1,), 

5058 ) 

5059 strides = context.make_tuple(builder, 

5060 types.UniTuple(types.intp, 1), 

5061 (ary.itemsize,)) 

5062 populate_array(ret, ary.data, shape, strides, ary.itemsize, 

5063 ary.meminfo, ary.parent) 

5064 return impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, retty, ret._getvalue()) 

5065 

5066 elif (retty.layout == aryty.layout 

5067 or (aryty.ndim == 1 and aryty.layout in 'CF')): 

5068 # 1-dim contiguous input => return the same array 

5069 return impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, retty, args[0]) 

5070 

5071 else: 

5072 if aryty.layout == 'A': 

5073 # There's still chance the array is in contiguous layout, 

5074 # just that we don't know at compile time. 

5075 # We can do a runtime check. 

5076 

5077 # Prepare and call is_contiguous or is_fortran 

5078 assert output_layout in 'CF' 

5079 check_func = is_contiguous if output_layout == 'C' else is_fortran 

5080 is_contig = _call_contiguous_check(check_func, 

5081 context, 

5082 builder, 

5083 aryty, 

5084 args[0]) 

5085 with builder.if_else(is_contig) as (then, orelse): 

5086 # If the array is already contiguous, just return it 

5087 with then: 

5088 out_then = impl_ret_borrowed(context, builder, retty, 

5089 args[0]) 

5090 then_blk = builder.block 

5091 # Otherwise, copy to a new contiguous region 

5092 with orelse: 

5093 out_orelse = _array_copy(context, builder, sig, args) 

5094 orelse_blk = builder.block 

5095 # Phi node for the return value 

5096 ret_phi = builder.phi(out_then.type) 

5097 ret_phi.add_incoming(out_then, then_blk) 

5098 ret_phi.add_incoming(out_orelse, orelse_blk) 

5099 return ret_phi 

5100 

5101 else: 

5102 # Return a copy with the right layout 

5103 return _array_copy(context, builder, sig, args) 

5104

5300 if ptr_dtype is not None and dtype != ptr_dtype: 

5301 msg = f"mismatching dtype '{dtype}' for pointer type '{ptr}'" 

5302 raise errors.NumbaTypeError(msg) 

5303 else: 

5304 msg = f"invalid dtype spec '{dtype_}'" 

5305 raise errors.NumbaTypeError(msg) 

5306 

5307 ndim = ty_parse_shape(shape) 

5308 if ndim is None: 

5309 msg = f"invalid shape '{shape}'" 

5310 raise errors.NumbaTypeError(msg) 

5311 

5312 retty = types.Array(dtype, ndim, layout) 

5313 sig = signature(retty, ptr, shape) 

5314 return sig, np_cfarray 

5315 return intrinsic_cfarray

5318def np_cfarray(context, builder, sig, args): 

5319 """ 

5320 numba.numpy_support.carray(...) and 

5321 numba.numpy_support.farray(...). 

5322 """ 

5323 ptrty, shapety = sig.args[:2] 

5324 ptr, shape = args[:2] 

5325 

5326 aryty = sig.return_type 

5327 assert aryty.layout in 'CF'

5334 if isinstance(shapety, types.BaseTuple): 

5335 shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, shape) 

5336 else: 

5337 shapety = (shapety,)

5363 meminfo=None,

5397def compute_sequence_shape(context, builder, ndim, seqty, seq): 

5398 """ 

5399 Compute the likely shape of a nested sequence (possibly 0d). 

5400 """ 

5401 intp_t = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

5402 zero = Constant(intp_t, 0) 

5403 

5404 def get_first_item(seqty, seq): 

5405 if isinstance(seqty, types.BaseTuple): 

5406 if len(seqty) == 0: 

5407 return None, None 

5408 else: 

5409 return seqty[0], builder.extract_value(seq, 0) 

5410 else: 

5411 getitem_impl = _get_borrowing_getitem(context, seqty) 

5412 return seqty.dtype, getitem_impl(builder, (seq, zero)) 

5413 

5414 # Compute shape by traversing the first element of each nested 

5415 # sequence 

5416 shapes = [] 

5417 innerty, inner = seqty, seq 

5418 

5419 for i in range(ndim): 

5420 if i > 0: 

5421 innerty, inner = get_first_item(innerty, inner) 

5422 shapes.append(_get_seq_size(context, builder, innerty, inner)) 

5423 

5424 return tuple(shapes) 

5425 

5426 

5427def check_sequence_shape(context, builder, seqty, seq, shapes): 

5428 """ 

5429 Check the nested sequence matches the given *shapes*. 

5430 """ 

5431 

5432 def _fail(): 

5433 context.call_conv.return_user_exc(builder, ValueError, 

5434 ("incompatible sequence shape",)) 

5435 

5436 def check_seq_size(seqty, seq, shapes): 

5437 if len(shapes) == 0: 

5438 return 

5439 

5440 size = _get_seq_size(context, builder, seqty, seq) 

5441 expected = shapes[0] 

5442 mismatch = builder.icmp_signed('!=', size, expected) 

5443 with builder.if_then(mismatch, likely=False): 

5444 _fail() 

5445 

5446 if len(shapes) == 1: 

5447 return 

5448 

5449 if isinstance(seqty, types.Sequence): 

5450 getitem_impl = _get_borrowing_getitem(context, seqty) 

5451 with cgutils.for_range(builder, size) as loop: 

5452 innerty = seqty.dtype 

5453 inner = getitem_impl(builder, (seq, loop.index)) 

5454 check_seq_size(innerty, inner, shapes[1:]) 

5455 

5456 elif isinstance(seqty, types.BaseTuple): 

5457 for i in range(len(seqty)): 

5458 innerty = seqty[i] 

5459 inner = builder.extract_value(seq, i) 

5460 check_seq_size(innerty, inner, shapes[1:]) 

5461 

5462 else: 

5463 assert 0, seqty 

5464 

5465 check_seq_size(seqty, seq, shapes)

5468def assign_sequence_to_array(context, builder, data, shapes, strides, 

5469 arrty, seqty, seq): 

5470 """ 

5471 Assign a nested sequence contents to an array. The shape must match 

5472 the sequence's structure. 

5473 """ 

5474 

5475 def assign_item(indices, valty, val): 

5476 ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, data, shapes, strides, 

5477 arrty.layout, indices, wraparound=False) 

5478 val = context.cast(builder, val, valty, arrty.dtype) 

5479 store_item(context, builder, arrty, val, ptr) 

5480 

5481 def assign(seqty, seq, shapes, indices): 

5482 if len(shapes) == 0: 

5483 assert not isinstance(seqty, (types.Sequence, types.BaseTuple)) 

5484 assign_item(indices, seqty, seq) 

5485 return 

5486 

5487 size = shapes[0] 

5488 

5489 if isinstance(seqty, types.Sequence): 

5490 getitem_impl = _get_borrowing_getitem(context, seqty) 

5491 with cgutils.for_range(builder, size) as loop: 

5492 innerty = seqty.dtype 

5493 inner = getitem_impl(builder, (seq, loop.index)) 

5494 assign(innerty, inner, shapes[1:], indices + (loop.index,)) 

5495 

5496 elif isinstance(seqty, types.BaseTuple): 

5497 for i in range(len(seqty)): 

5498 innerty = seqty[i] 

5499 inner = builder.extract_value(seq, i) 

5500 index = context.get_constant(types.intp, i) 

5501 assign(innerty, inner, shapes[1:], indices + (index,)) 

5502 

5503 else: 

5504 assert 0, seqty 

5505 

5506 assign(seqty, seq, shapes, ())

5561def _normalize_axis(context, builder, func_name, ndim, axis): 

5562 zero = axis.type(0) 

5563 ll_ndim = axis.type(ndim) 

5564 

5565 # Normalize negative axis 

5566 is_neg_axis = builder.icmp_signed('<', axis, zero) 

5567 axis = builder.select(is_neg_axis, builder.add(axis, ll_ndim), axis) 

5568 

5569 # Check axis for bounds 

5570 axis_out_of_bounds = builder.or_( 

5571 builder.icmp_signed('<', axis, zero), 

5572 builder.icmp_signed('>=', axis, ll_ndim)) 

5573 with builder.if_then(axis_out_of_bounds, likely=False): 

5574 msg = "%s(): axis out of bounds" % func_name 

5575 context.call_conv.return_user_exc(builder, IndexError, (msg,)) 

5576 

5577 return axis

5580def _insert_axis_in_shape(context, builder, orig_shape, ndim, axis): 

5581 """ 

5582 Compute shape with the new axis inserted 

5583 e.g. given original shape (2, 3, 4) and axis=2, 

5584 the returned new shape is (2, 3, 1, 4). 

5585 """ 

5586 assert len(orig_shape) == ndim - 1 

5587 

5588 ll_shty = ir.ArrayType(cgutils.intp_t, ndim) 

5589 shapes = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ll_shty) 

5590 

5591 one = cgutils.intp_t(1) 

5592 

5593 # 1. copy original sizes at appropriate places 

5594 for dim in range(ndim - 1): 

5595 ll_dim = cgutils.intp_t(dim) 

5596 after_axis = builder.icmp_signed('>=', ll_dim, axis) 

5597 sh = orig_shape[dim] 

5598 idx = builder.select(after_axis, 

5599 builder.add(ll_dim, one), 

5600 ll_dim) 

5601 builder.store(sh, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, shapes, 0, idx)) 

5602 

5603 # 2. insert new size (1) at axis dimension 

5604 builder.store(one, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, shapes, 0, axis)) 

5605 

5606 return cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, builder.load(shapes)) 

5607 

5608 

5609def _insert_axis_in_strides(context, builder, orig_strides, ndim, axis): 

5610 """ 

5611 Same as _insert_axis_in_shape(), but with a strides array. 

5612 """ 

5613 assert len(orig_strides) == ndim - 1 

5614 

5615 ll_shty = ir.ArrayType(cgutils.intp_t, ndim) 

5616 strides = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ll_shty) 

5617 

5618 one = cgutils.intp_t(1) 

5619 zero = cgutils.intp_t(0) 

5620 

5621 # 1. copy original strides at appropriate places 

5622 for dim in range(ndim - 1): 

5623 ll_dim = cgutils.intp_t(dim) 

5624 after_axis = builder.icmp_signed('>=', ll_dim, axis) 

5625 idx = builder.select(after_axis, 

5626 builder.add(ll_dim, one), 

5627 ll_dim) 

5628 builder.store(orig_strides[dim], 

5629 cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, strides, 0, idx)) 

5630 

5631 # 2. insert new stride at axis dimension 

5632 # (the value is indifferent for a 1-sized dimension, we use 0) 

5633 builder.store(zero, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, strides, 0, axis)) 

5634 

5635 return cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, builder.load(strides))

5764def _do_concatenate(context, builder, axis, 

5765 arrtys, arrs, arr_shapes, arr_strides, 

5766 retty, ret_shapes): 

5767 """ 

5768 Concatenate arrays along the given axis. 

5769 """ 

5770 assert len(arrtys) == len(arrs) == len(arr_shapes) == len(arr_strides) 

5771 

5772 zero = cgutils.intp_t(0) 

5773 

5774 # Allocate return array 

5775 ret = _empty_nd_impl(context, builder, retty, ret_shapes) 

5776 ret_strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, ret.strides) 

5777 

5778 # Compute the offset by which to bump the destination pointer 

5779 # after copying each input array. 

5780 # Morally, we need to copy each input array at different start indices 

5781 # into the destination array; bumping the destination pointer 

5782 # is simply easier than offsetting all destination indices. 

5783 copy_offsets = [] 

5784 

5785 for arr_sh in arr_shapes: 

5786 # offset = ret_strides[axis] * input_shape[axis] 

5787 offset = zero 

5788 for dim, (size, stride) in enumerate(zip(arr_sh, ret_strides)): 

5789 is_axis = builder.icmp_signed('==', axis.type(dim), axis) 

5790 addend = builder.mul(size, stride) 

5791 offset = builder.select(is_axis, 

5792 builder.add(offset, addend), 

5793 offset) 

5794 copy_offsets.append(offset) 

5795 

5796 # Copy input arrays into the return array 

5797 ret_data = ret.data 

5798 

5799 for arrty, arr, arr_sh, arr_st, offset in zip(arrtys, arrs, arr_shapes, 

5800 arr_strides, copy_offsets): 

5801 arr_data = arr.data 

5802 

5803 # Do the copy loop 

5804 # Note the loop nesting is optimized for the destination layout 

5805 loop_nest = cgutils.loop_nest(builder, arr_sh, cgutils.intp_t, 

5806 order=retty.layout) 

5807 

5808 with loop_nest as indices: 

5809 src_ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, arr_data, 

5810 arr_sh, arr_st, 

5811 arrty.layout, indices) 

5812 val = load_item(context, builder, arrty, src_ptr) 

5813 val = context.cast(builder, val, arrty.dtype, retty.dtype) 

5814 dest_ptr = cgutils.get_item_pointer2(context, builder, ret_data, 

5815 ret_shapes, ret_strides, 

5816 retty.layout, indices) 

5817 store_item(context, builder, retty, val, dest_ptr) 

5818 

5819 # Bump destination pointer 

5820 ret_data = cgutils.pointer_add(builder, ret_data, offset) 

5821 

5822 return ret 

5823 

5824 

5825def _np_concatenate(context, builder, arrtys, arrs, retty, axis): 

5826 ndim = retty.ndim 

5827 

5828 arrs = [make_array(aty)(context, builder, value=a) 

5829 for aty, a in zip(arrtys, arrs)] 

5830 

5831 axis = _normalize_axis(context, builder, "np.concatenate", ndim, axis) 

5832 

5833 # Get input shapes 

5834 arr_shapes = [cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape) for arr in arrs] 

5835 arr_strides = [cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.strides) for arr in arrs] 

5836 

5837 # Compute return shape: 

5838 # - the dimension for the concatenation axis is summed over all inputs 

5839 # - other dimensions must match exactly for each input 

5840 ret_shapes = [cgutils.alloca_once_value(builder, sh) 

5841 for sh in arr_shapes[0]] 

5842 

5843 for dim in range(ndim): 

5844 is_axis = builder.icmp_signed('==', axis.type(dim), axis) 

5845 ret_shape_ptr = ret_shapes[dim] 

5846 ret_sh = builder.load(ret_shape_ptr) 

5847 other_shapes = [sh[dim] for sh in arr_shapes[1:]] 

5848 

5849 with builder.if_else(is_axis) as (on_axis, on_other_dim): 

5850 with on_axis: 

5851 sh = functools.reduce( 

5852 builder.add, 

5853 other_shapes + [ret_sh]) 

5854 builder.store(sh, ret_shape_ptr) 

5855 

5856 with on_other_dim: 

5857 is_ok = cgutils.true_bit 

5858 for sh in other_shapes: 

5859 is_ok = builder.and_(is_ok, 

5860 builder.icmp_signed('==', sh, ret_sh)) 

5861 with builder.if_then(builder.not_(is_ok), likely=False): 

5862 context.call_conv.return_user_exc( 

5863 builder, ValueError, 

5864 ("np.concatenate(): input sizes over " 

5865 "dimension %d do not match" % dim,)) 

5866 

5867 ret_shapes = [builder.load(sh) for sh in ret_shapes] 

5868 

5869 ret = _do_concatenate(context, builder, axis, 

5870 arrtys, arrs, arr_shapes, arr_strides, 

5871 retty, ret_shapes) 

5872 return impl_ret_new_ref(context, builder, retty, ret._getvalue()) 

5873

5885 axis = _normalize_axis(context, builder, "np.stack", ndim, axis) 

5886 

5887 # Check input arrays have the same shape 

5888 orig_shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arrs[0].shape) 

5889 

5890 for arr in arrs[1:]: 

5891 is_ok = cgutils.true_bit 

5892 for sh, orig_sh in zip(cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.shape), 

5893 orig_shape): 

5894 is_ok = builder.and_(is_ok, builder.icmp_signed('==', sh, orig_sh)) 

5895 with builder.if_then(builder.not_(is_ok), likely=False): 

5896 context.call_conv.return_user_exc( 

5897 builder, ValueError, 

5898 ("np.stack(): all input arrays must have the same shape",)) 

5899 

5900 orig_strides = [cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, arr.strides) for arr in arrs] 

5901 

5902 # Compute input shapes and return shape with the new axis inserted 

5903 # e.g. given 5 input arrays of shape (2, 3, 4) and axis=1, 

5904 # corrected input shape is (2, 1, 3, 4) and return shape is (2, 5, 3, 4). 

5905 ll_shty = ir.ArrayType(cgutils.intp_t, ndim) 

5906 

5907 input_shapes = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ll_shty) 

5908 ret_shapes = cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ll_shty) 

5909 

5910 # 1. copy original sizes at appropriate places 

5911 for dim in range(ndim - 1): 

5912 ll_dim = cgutils.intp_t(dim) 

5913 after_axis = builder.icmp_signed('>=', ll_dim, axis) 

5914 sh = orig_shape[dim] 

5915 idx = builder.select(after_axis, 

5916 builder.add(ll_dim, one), 

5917 ll_dim) 

5918 builder.store(sh, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, input_shapes, 0, idx)) 

5919 builder.store(sh, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, ret_shapes, 0, idx)) 

5920 

5921 # 2. insert new size at axis dimension 

5922 builder.store(one, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, input_shapes, 0, axis)) 

5923 builder.store(ll_narrays, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, 

5924 ret_shapes, 

5925 0, 

5926 axis)) 

5927 

5928 input_shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, builder.load(input_shapes)) 

5929 input_shapes = [input_shapes] * len(arrs) 

5930 ret_shapes = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, builder.load(ret_shapes)) 

5931 

5932 # Compute input strides for each array with the new axis inserted 

5933 input_strides = [cgutils.alloca_once(builder, ll_shty) 

5934 for i in range(len(arrs))] 

5935 

5936 # 1. copy original strides at appropriate places 

5937 for dim in range(ndim - 1): 

5938 ll_dim = cgutils.intp_t(dim) 

5939 after_axis = builder.icmp_signed('>=', ll_dim, axis) 

5940 idx = builder.select(after_axis, 

5941 builder.add(ll_dim, one), 

5942 ll_dim) 

5943 for i in range(len(arrs)): 

5944 builder.store(orig_strides[i][dim], 

5945 cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, input_strides[i], 0, 

5946 idx)) 

5947 

5948 # 2. insert new stride at axis dimension 

5949 # (the value is indifferent for a 1-sized dimension, we put 0) 

5950 for i in range(len(arrs)): 

5951 builder.store(zero, cgutils.gep_inbounds(builder, input_strides[i], 0, 

5952 axis)) 

5953 

5954 input_strides = [cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, builder.load(st)) 

5955 for st in input_strides] 

5956 

5957 # Create concatenated array 

5958 ret = _do_concatenate(context, builder, axis, 

5959 arrtys, arrs, input_shapes, input_strides, 

5960 retty, ret_shapes) 

5961 return impl_ret_new_ref(context, builder, retty, ret._getvalue())

6007def _column_stack_dims(context, func_name, arrays): 

6008 # column_stack() allows stacking 1-d and 2-d arrays together 

6009 for a in arrays:

6282@intrinsic 

6283def _build_flip_slice_tuple(tyctx, sz): 

6284 """ Creates a tuple of slices for np.flip indexing like 

6285 `(slice(None, None, -1),) * sz` """ 

6286 if not isinstance(sz, types.IntegerLiteral): 

6287 raise errors.RequireLiteralValue(sz) 

6288 size = int(sz.literal_value) 

6289 tuple_type = types.UniTuple(dtype=types.slice3_type, count=size) 

6290 sig = tuple_type(sz) 

6291 

6292 def codegen(context, builder, signature, args): 

6293 def impl(length, empty_tuple): 

6294 out = empty_tuple 

6295 for i in range(length): 

6296 out = tuple_setitem(out, i, slice(None, None, -1)) 

6297 return out 

6298 

6299 inner_argtypes = [types.intp, tuple_type] 

6300 inner_sig = typing.signature(tuple_type, *inner_argtypes) 

6301 ll_idx_type = context.get_value_type(types.intp) 

6302 # Allocate an empty tuple 

6303 empty_tuple = context.get_constant_undef(tuple_type) 

6304 inner_args = [ll_idx_type(size), empty_tuple] 

6305 

6306 res = context.compile_internal(builder, impl, inner_sig, inner_args) 

6307 return res 

6308

6326@overload(np.array_split)

6340 l, rem = divmod(ary.shape[axis], indices_or_sections)

6377 out = [] 

6378 prev = 0 

6379 for cur in literal_unroll(indices_or_sections): 

6380 idx = tuple_setitem(slice_tup, axis, slice(prev, cur)) 

6381 out.append(ary[idx]) 

6382 prev = cur

6491def get_sort_func(kind, lt_impl, is_argsort=False): 

6492 """ 

6493 Get a sort implementation of the given kind. 

6494 """ 

6495 key = kind, lt_impl.__name__, is_argsort 

6496 

6497 try: 

6498 return _sorts[key] 

6499 except KeyError: 

6500 if kind == 'quicksort': 

6501 sort = quicksort.make_jit_quicksort( 

6502 lt=lt_impl, 

6503 is_argsort=is_argsort, 

6504 is_np_array=True) 

6505 func = sort.run_quicksort 

6506 elif kind == 'mergesort': 

6507 sort = mergesort.make_jit_mergesort( 

6508 lt=lt_impl, 

6509 is_argsort=is_argsort) 

6510 func = sort.run_mergesort 

6511 _sorts[key] = func 

6512 return func

6609def reshape_unchecked(a, shape, strides): 

6610 """ 

6611 An intrinsic returning a derived array with the given shape and strides.

6613 raise NotImplementedError

6616@extending.type_callable(reshape_unchecked) 

6617def type_reshape_unchecked(context): 

6618 def check_shape(shape): 

6619 return (isinstance(shape, types.BaseTuple) and 

6620 all(isinstance(v, types.Integer) for v in shape)) 

6621 

6622 def typer(a, shape, strides): 

6623 if not isinstance(a, types.Array): 

6624 return 

6625 if not check_shape(shape) or not check_shape(strides): 

6626 return 

6627 if len(shape) != len(strides): 

6628 return 

6629 return a.copy(ndim=len(shape), layout='A') 

6630 

6631 return typer

6634@lower_builtin(reshape_unchecked, types.Array, types.BaseTuple, types.BaseTuple) 

6635def impl_shape_unchecked(context, builder, sig, args):

6637 retty = sig.return_type

6640 out = make_array(retty)(context, builder) 

6641 shape = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, args[1]) 

6642 strides = cgutils.unpack_tuple(builder, args[2])

6644 populate_array(out, 

6645 data=ary.data, 

6646 shape=shape, 

6647 strides=strides,

6656@extending.overload(np.lib.stride_tricks.as_strided) 

6657def as_strided(x, shape=None, strides=None): 

6658 if shape in (None, types.none): 

6659 @register_jitable 

6660 def get_shape(x, shape): 

6661 return x.shape 

6662 else: 

6663 @register_jitable 

6664 def get_shape(x, shape): 

6665 return shape 

6666 

6667 if strides in (None, types.none): 

6668 # When *strides* is not passed, as_strided() does a non-size-checking 

6669 # reshape(), possibly changing the original strides. This is too 

6670 # cumbersome to support right now, and a Web search shows all example 

6671 # use cases of as_strided() pass explicit *strides*. 

6672 raise errors.TypingError("as_strided() strides argument cannot be None") 

6673 else: 

6674 @register_jitable 

6675 def get_strides(x, strides): 

6676 return strides 

6677 

6678 def as_strided_impl(x, shape=None, strides=None): 

6679 x = reshape_unchecked(x, get_shape(x, shape), get_strides(x, strides)) 

6680 return x

6685@extending.overload(np.lib.stride_tricks.sliding_window_view) 

6686def sliding_window_view(x, window_shape, axis=None): 

6687 

6688 # Window shape must be given as either an integer or tuple of integers. 

6689 # We also need to generate buffer tuples we can modify to contain the 

6690 # final shape and strides (reshape_unchecked does not accept lists). 

6691 if isinstance(window_shape, types.Integer): 

6692 shape_buffer = tuple(range(x.ndim + 1)) 

6693 stride_buffer = tuple(range(x.ndim + 1)) 

6694 

6695 @register_jitable 

6696 def get_window_shape(window_shape): 

6697 return (window_shape,) 

6698 

6699 elif (isinstance(window_shape, types.UniTuple) and 

6700 isinstance(window_shape.dtype, types.Integer)): 

6701 shape_buffer = tuple(range(x.ndim + len(window_shape))) 

6702 stride_buffer = tuple(range(x.ndim + len(window_shape))) 

6703 

6704 @register_jitable 

6705 def get_window_shape(window_shape): 

6706 return window_shape 

6707 

6708 else: 

6709 raise errors.TypingError( 

6710 "window_shape must be an integer or tuple of integers" 

6711 ) 

6712 

6713 # Axis must be integer, tuple of integers, or None for all axes. 

6714 if is_nonelike(axis): 

6715 @register_jitable 

6716 def get_axis(window_shape, axis, ndim): 

6717 return list(range(ndim)) 

6718 

6719 elif isinstance(axis, types.Integer): 

6720 @register_jitable 

6721 def get_axis(window_shape, axis, ndim): 

6722 return [ 

6723 normalize_axis("sliding_window_view", "axis", ndim, axis) 

6724 ] 

6725 

6726 elif (isinstance(axis, types.UniTuple) and 

6727 isinstance(axis.dtype, types.Integer)): 

6728 @register_jitable 

6729 def get_axis(window_shape, axis, ndim): 

6730 return [normalize_axis("sliding_window_view", "axis", ndim, a) 

6731 for a in axis] 

6732 

6733 else: 

6734 raise errors.TypingError( 

6735 "axis must be None, an integer or tuple of integers" 

6736 ) 

6737 

6738 def sliding_window_view_impl(x, window_shape, axis=None): 

6739 window_shape = get_window_shape(window_shape) 

6740 axis = get_axis(window_shape, axis, x.ndim) 

6741 if len(window_shape) != len(axis): 

6742 raise ValueError( 

6743 "Must provide matching length window_shape and axis" 

6744 ) 

6745 

6746 # Initialise view details with shape and strides of x. 

6747 out_shape = shape_buffer 

6748 out_strides = stride_buffer 

6749 for i in range(x.ndim): 

6750 out_shape = tuple_setitem(out_shape, i, x.shape[i]) 

6751 out_strides = tuple_setitem(out_strides, i, x.strides[i]) 

6752 

6753 # Trim the dimensions being windowed and set the window shape and 

6754 # strides. Note: the same axis can be windowed repeatedly. 

6755 i = x.ndim 

6756 for ax, dim in zip(axis, window_shape): 

6757 if dim < 0: 

6758 raise ValueError( 

6759 "`window_shape` cannot contain negative values" 

6760 ) 

6761 if out_shape[ax] < dim: 

6762 raise ValueError( 

6763 "window_shape cannot be larger than input array shape" 

6764 ) 

6765 

6766 trimmed = out_shape[ax] - dim + 1 

6767 out_shape = tuple_setitem(out_shape, ax, trimmed) 

6768 out_shape = tuple_setitem(out_shape, i, dim) 

6769 out_strides = tuple_setitem(out_strides, i, x.strides[ax]) 

6770 i += 1 

6771 

6772 # The NumPy version calls as_strided, but our implementation of 

6773 # as_strided is effectively a wrapper for reshape_unchecked. 

6774 view = reshape_unchecked(x, out_shape, out_strides) 

6775 return view 

6776 

6777 return sliding_window_view_impl

6827@register_jitable 

6828def _take_along_axis_impl( 

6829 arr, indices, axis, Ni_orig, Nk_orig, indices_broadcast_shape 

6830): 

6831 # Based on example code in 

6832 # https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/623bc1fae1d47df24e7f1e29321d0c0ba2771ce0/numpy/lib/shape_base.py#L90-L103 

6833 # With addition of pre-broadcasting: 

6834 # https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/19704 

6835 

6836 # Wrap axis, it's used in tuple_setitem so must be (axis >= 0) to ensure 

6837 # the GEP is in bounds. 

6838 axis = normalize_axis("np.take_along_axis", "axis", arr.ndim, axis) 

6839 

6840 # Broadcast the two arrays to matching shapes: 

6841 arr_shape = list(arr.shape) 

6842 arr_shape[axis] = 1 

6843 for i, (d1, d2) in enumerate(zip(arr_shape, indices.shape)): 

6844 if d1 == 1: 

6845 new_val = d2 

6846 elif d2 == 1: 

6847 new_val = d1 

6848 else: 

6849 if d1 != d2: 

6850 raise ValueError( 

6851 "`arr` and `indices` dimensions don't match" 

6852 ) 

6853 new_val = d1 

6854 indices_broadcast_shape = tuple_setitem( 

6855 indices_broadcast_shape, i, new_val 

6856 ) 

6857 arr_broadcast_shape = tuple_setitem( 

6858 indices_broadcast_shape, axis, arr.shape[axis] 

6859 ) 

6860 arr = np.broadcast_to(arr, arr_broadcast_shape) 

6861 indices = np.broadcast_to(indices, indices_broadcast_shape) 

6862 

6863 Ni = Ni_orig 

6864 if len(Ni_orig) > 0: 

6865 for i in range(len(Ni)): 

6866 Ni = tuple_setitem(Ni, i, arr.shape[i]) 

6867 Nk = Nk_orig 

6868 if len(Nk_orig) > 0: 

6869 for i in range(len(Nk)): 

6870 Nk = tuple_setitem(Nk, i, arr.shape[axis + 1 + i]) 

6871 

6872 J = indices.shape[axis] # Need not equal M 

6873 out = np.empty(Ni + (J,) + Nk, arr.dtype) 

6874 

6875 np_s_ = (slice(None, None, None),) 

6876 

6877 for ii in np.ndindex(Ni): 

6878 for kk in np.ndindex(Nk): 

6879 a_1d = arr[ii + np_s_ + kk] 

6880 indices_1d = indices[ii + np_s_ + kk] 

6881 out_1d = out[ii + np_s_ + kk] 

6882 for j in range(J): 

6883 out_1d[j] = a_1d[indices_1d[j]] 

6884 return out

6931@overload(np.nan_to_num) 

6932def nan_to_num_impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6933 if isinstance(x, types.Number): 

6934 if isinstance(x, types.Integer): 

6935 # Integers do not have nans or infs 

6936 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6937 return x 

6938 

6939 elif isinstance(x, types.Float): 

6940 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6941 if np.isnan(x): 

6942 return nan 

6943 elif np.isneginf(x): 

6944 return np.finfo(type(x)).min 

6945 elif np.isposinf(x): 

6946 return np.finfo(type(x)).max 

6947 return x 

6948 elif isinstance(x, types.Complex): 

6949 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6950 r = np.nan_to_num(x.real, nan=nan) 

6951 c = np.nan_to_num(x.imag, nan=nan) 

6952 return complex(r, c) 

6953 else: 

6954 raise errors.TypingError( 

6955 "Only Integer, Float, and Complex values are accepted" 

6956 ) 

6957 

6958 elif type_can_asarray(x): 

6959 if isinstance(x.dtype, types.Integer): 

6960 # Integers do not have nans or infs 

6961 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6962 return x 

6963 elif isinstance(x.dtype, types.Float): 

6964 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6965 min_inf = np.finfo(x.dtype).min 

6966 max_inf = np.finfo(x.dtype).max 

6967 

6968 x_ = np.asarray(x) 

6969 output = np.copy(x_) if copy else x_ 

6970 

6971 output_flat = output.flat 

6972 for i in range(output.size): 

6973 if np.isnan(output_flat[i]): 

6974 output_flat[i] = nan 

6975 elif np.isneginf(output_flat[i]): 

6976 output_flat[i] = min_inf 

6977 elif np.isposinf(output_flat[i]): 

6978 output_flat[i] = max_inf 

6979 return output 

6980 elif isinstance(x.dtype, types.Complex): 

6981 def impl(x, copy=True, nan=0.0): 

6982 x_ = np.asarray(x) 

6983 output = np.copy(x_) if copy else x_ 

6984 

6985 np.nan_to_num(output.real, copy=False, nan=nan) 

6986 np.nan_to_num(output.imag, copy=False, nan=nan) 

6987 return output 

6988 else: 

6989 raise errors.TypingError( 

6990 "Only Integer, Float, and Complex values are accepted" 

6991 ) 

6992 else: 

6993 raise errors.TypingError("The first argument must be a scalar or an " 

6994 "array-like") 

6995 return impl
